WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.419 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.419 --> 00:00:09.820 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:09.820 --> 00:00:19.674 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.674 --> 00:00:21.840 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: We're
all familiar with the terms

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:23.160 align:middle line:10%
meme and zeitgeist.

00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:25.620 align:middle line:10%
But how many of you
have heard of egregores?

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:28.470 align:middle line:84%
Mark Stavish is here today
to share his research

00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:30.450 align:middle line:84%
on the effect of
collective belief

00:00:30.450 --> 00:00:33.900 align:middle line:84%
and its extension called
egregores, virtual beings that

00:00:33.900 --> 00:00:36.960 align:middle line:84%
can influence, even control
our collective experience

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:38.700 align:middle line:90%
and individual choices.

00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:40.857 align:middle line:84%
Welcome, Mark, what
a fascinating book.

00:00:40.857 --> 00:00:41.940 align:middle line:90%
>>MARK STAVISH: Thank you.

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:43.064 align:middle line:90%
It's a pleasure to be here.

00:00:43.064 --> 00:00:45.300 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: You know,
and it brings up some,

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:50.280 align:middle line:10%
I think it really helps clarify
some issues we have about

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:53.700 align:middle line:10%
controlling forces because
so many people watching this

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:56.130 align:middle line:10%
have come to accept
that we have guides,

00:00:56.130 --> 00:00:58.110 align:middle line:10%
that there are dark entities.

00:00:58.110 --> 00:01:00.360 align:middle line:84%
And certainly, Hollywood
has done its share

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:02.610 align:middle line:90%
of pumping that notion up.

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:05.730 align:middle line:84%
But the way you handle it is
very intelligent because a lot

00:01:05.730 --> 00:01:07.680 align:middle line:90%
of it has to do with us.

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:10.050 align:middle line:84%
It has to do with
what we've personally

00:01:10.050 --> 00:01:12.240 align:middle line:90%
created within our own minds.

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:16.330 align:middle line:84%
And so let's go ahead and
start with a definition.

00:01:16.330 --> 00:01:17.730 align:middle line:90%
What is an egregore?

00:01:17.730 --> 00:01:20.340 align:middle line:84%
And I've written a whole
bunch of different notions

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:24.330 align:middle line:84%
in your book of what is
considered to be an egregore.

00:01:24.330 --> 00:01:25.610 align:middle line:90%
Define egregore first.

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:27.720 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, an
egregore, it's a Greek word.

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:29.110 align:middle line:90%
And no one says it properly.

00:01:29.110 --> 00:01:29.970 align:middle line:10%
You're the best.

00:01:29.970 --> 00:01:31.750 align:middle line:10%
You've come closest to anyone.

00:01:31.750 --> 00:01:32.910 align:middle line:10%
I think egregore.

00:01:32.910 --> 00:01:33.990 align:middle line:90%
And someone told me--

00:01:33.990 --> 00:01:35.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I wouldn't
have guessed that.

00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:36.660 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Someone told me
it's like the first g is

00:01:36.660 --> 00:01:37.890 align:middle line:90%
silent as in gnome.

00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:38.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, OK.

00:01:38.920 --> 00:01:39.939 align:middle line:90%
No, I didn't get it.

00:01:39.939 --> 00:01:41.230 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: It's potato, potato.

00:01:41.230 --> 00:01:42.870 align:middle line:84%
So we just go with
what we've got.

00:01:42.870 --> 00:01:46.890 align:middle line:84%
And it really is a
collective consciousness.

00:01:46.890 --> 00:01:48.910 align:middle line:84%
And people are familiar
with that term,

00:01:48.910 --> 00:01:52.380 align:middle line:84%
particularly from Jungian
studies and psychology.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.700 align:middle line:84%
But we have to ask,
how does it function?

00:01:54.700 --> 00:01:57.730 align:middle line:84%
And that's what makes an
egregore very important.

00:01:57.730 --> 00:02:01.600 align:middle line:84%
So an egregore is really a
social control mechanism.

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:03.510 align:middle line:90%
It's a limiting factor.

00:02:03.510 --> 00:02:05.880 align:middle line:84%
Because whenever we're within
a group, there are certain

00:02:05.880 --> 00:02:09.660 align:middle line:84%
limits as to our thoughts and
actions within that group.

00:02:09.660 --> 00:02:11.234 align:middle line:84%
But we often don't
think about it.

00:02:11.234 --> 00:02:12.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No we don't.

00:02:12.150 --> 00:02:14.910 align:middle line:84%
And it's influencing us all
the time, whether we know it

00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:16.740 align:middle line:90%
or not.

00:02:16.740 --> 00:02:19.397 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Probably one of
the most disturbing aspects

00:02:19.397 --> 00:02:21.480 align:middle line:84%
of this book is when people
read it, they suddenly

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:24.300 align:middle line:84%
realize how many egregores
or collective awarenesses

00:02:24.300 --> 00:02:25.890 align:middle line:90%
they're involved with.

00:02:25.890 --> 00:02:28.590 align:middle line:84%
And it often brings
with it this sense

00:02:28.590 --> 00:02:29.797 align:middle line:90%
of helplessness or denial.

00:02:29.797 --> 00:02:31.630 align:middle line:84%
Like what do you mean
I'm involved with this

00:02:31.630 --> 00:02:33.089 align:middle line:84%
or these things
are influencing me?

00:02:33.089 --> 00:02:35.005 align:middle line:84%
But when you step back
and you think about it,

00:02:35.005 --> 00:02:36.930 align:middle line:84%
you realize, well,
I'm involved with I

00:02:36.930 --> 00:02:38.400 align:middle line:90%
have an egregore at work.

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:40.320 align:middle line:90%
We call it a corporate culture.

00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:42.570 align:middle line:84%
We have an egregore
maybe in our community.

00:02:42.570 --> 00:02:44.550 align:middle line:84%
We call that
community standards.

00:02:44.550 --> 00:02:47.280 align:middle line:84%
We have an egregore in
our spiritual groups

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:51.390 align:middle line:84%
or spiritual practices
and even with our family.

00:02:51.390 --> 00:02:55.260 align:middle line:84%
But these are different types
of collective awarenesses.

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:58.980 align:middle line:84%
And some of them, we
voluntarily get involved with,

00:02:58.980 --> 00:03:01.854 align:middle line:90%
others just by our geography.

00:03:01.854 --> 00:03:03.270 align:middle line:84%
But what makes
this interesting is

00:03:03.270 --> 00:03:05.550 align:middle line:84%
that there's two
definitions to an egregore

00:03:05.550 --> 00:03:07.480 align:middle line:90%
or two descriptions of them.

00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:09.030 align:middle line:84%
One of them is the
classical notion.

00:03:09.030 --> 00:03:11.340 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I like
to focus on with folks.

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:13.080 align:middle line:84%
And the other is
the modern notion.

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:15.480 align:middle line:84%
The modern notion is
this collective awareness

00:03:15.480 --> 00:03:18.420 align:middle line:84%
comes together any time
we have a group of people

00:03:18.420 --> 00:03:20.500 align:middle line:84%
forming a group for a
particular activity.

00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:21.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:22.500 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So that means
some of these egregores

00:03:22.500 --> 00:03:23.300 align:middle line:90%
can come and go.

00:03:23.300 --> 00:03:25.870 align:middle line:90%


00:03:25.870 --> 00:03:27.990 align:middle line:84%
Then you have the
classical notion,

00:03:27.990 --> 00:03:32.100 align:middle line:84%
which has us down here on
terra firma and some kind

00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:35.350 align:middle line:84%
of psychic or spiritual
entity on the other end

00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:38.510 align:middle line:84%
and this conduit of energy
that connects the two.

00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:40.540 align:middle line:90%
And that's the classical notion.

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:44.730 align:middle line:84%
So I think for viewers, one
of the things about egregores

00:03:44.730 --> 00:03:49.050 align:middle line:84%
that they need to focus
on is their philosophical

00:03:49.050 --> 00:03:51.892 align:middle line:84%
and spiritual and
political egregores

00:03:51.892 --> 00:03:53.850 align:middle line:84%
are the ones that will
often have the strongest

00:03:53.850 --> 00:03:54.650 align:middle line:90%
pull on them.

00:03:54.650 --> 00:03:56.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, and they
certainly do right now

00:03:56.970 --> 00:04:00.790 align:middle line:84%
in the world at large and
in the US in particular.

00:04:00.790 --> 00:04:03.032 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: When we
look at the involvement

00:04:03.032 --> 00:04:04.490 align:middle line:84%
that we have in
various groups, one

00:04:04.490 --> 00:04:05.870 align:middle line:84%
of the things we have
to notice particularly

00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:08.610 align:middle line:84%
in our spiritual activities
and our political activities

00:04:08.610 --> 00:04:10.764 align:middle line:84%
is that they always
seek to involve us

00:04:10.764 --> 00:04:12.180 align:middle line:84%
into identification
with something

00:04:12.180 --> 00:04:13.120 align:middle line:90%
bigger than ourselves.

00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:15.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's wonderful because
we want to contribute.

00:04:15.570 --> 00:04:17.800 align:middle line:84%
We want our lives to
have value and meaning.

00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:20.670 align:middle line:84%
So we often want to
associate with a movement

00:04:20.670 --> 00:04:23.311 align:middle line:84%
that promises to make
the world a better place.

00:04:23.311 --> 00:04:25.560 align:middle line:84%
But what we notice with
particular spiritual movements

00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:28.860 align:middle line:84%
and political movements
is that the egregore

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:32.790 align:middle line:84%
becomes an end in and of
itself in that it essentially

00:04:32.790 --> 00:04:34.650 align:middle line:90%
abuses our goodwill.

00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:37.320 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
points of the book

00:04:37.320 --> 00:04:40.500 align:middle line:84%
is to get people to ask
themselves a question, what

00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:42.990 align:middle line:90%
is it I want my life to mean?

00:04:42.990 --> 00:04:46.270 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to achieve
that goal of meaning?

00:04:46.270 --> 00:04:49.920 align:middle line:84%
And when I participate in
these group activities,

00:04:49.920 --> 00:04:51.790 align:middle line:84%
am I getting out of
what I was promised?

00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:52.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:04:52.590 --> 00:04:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And when we get toward the
last part of this interview,

00:04:56.080 --> 00:05:00.600 align:middle line:84%
we're going to really go into
the essentially self help

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:03.090 align:middle line:84%
element of this of how
we break those control

00:05:03.090 --> 00:05:04.860 align:middle line:90%
mechanisms over our lives.

00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:07.230 align:middle line:84%
But first, I think it's good
to really establish just

00:05:07.230 --> 00:05:09.420 align:middle line:84%
how deeply they
reach into our lives.

00:05:09.420 --> 00:05:10.470 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, just
take a look at the news.

00:05:10.470 --> 00:05:12.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, identity politics
is politics today.

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:13.145 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:13.145 --> 00:05:14.520 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And
it's always if you

00:05:14.520 --> 00:05:16.144 align:middle line:84%
look at how people
are being described,

00:05:16.144 --> 00:05:18.590 align:middle line:84%
it's always in terms of
membership in a group

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:21.350 align:middle line:84%
as if that is the major
or primary defining

00:05:21.350 --> 00:05:24.260 align:middle line:90%
characteristics of their being.

00:05:24.260 --> 00:05:27.690 align:middle line:84%
Well, for some people, it may
be, but maybe not for everyone.

00:05:27.690 --> 00:05:32.560 align:middle line:84%
So the more we identify with
just these narrow identifiers

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:33.360 align:middle line:90%
is what it is.

00:05:33.360 --> 00:05:34.380 align:middle line:90%
It's a narrowing factor.

00:05:34.380 --> 00:05:35.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:35.180 --> 00:05:37.596 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Then we don't think
about things outside of it.

00:05:37.596 --> 00:05:40.065 align:middle line:84%
That's why I said it's a
social control mechanism.

00:05:40.065 --> 00:05:40.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:05:40.940 --> 00:05:43.100 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at this
mechanically for a moment.

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:46.530 align:middle line:84%
So we know in the world
of the quantum reality

00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:48.950 align:middle line:84%
that thoughts are things,
that everything is a thought,

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:51.470 align:middle line:84%
and it forms itself,
a thought form that

00:05:51.470 --> 00:05:57.070 align:middle line:84%
ultimately creates through time,
intention, care, dedication.

00:05:57.070 --> 00:05:59.630 align:middle line:84%
It will sink down into a
physical reality, whether it's

00:05:59.630 --> 00:06:01.820 align:middle line:84%
someone that's dreamt
of a painting that

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:04.640 align:middle line:84%
becomes reality or a show
between the two of us sitting

00:06:04.640 --> 00:06:05.960 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:06:05.960 --> 00:06:10.070 align:middle line:84%
So on the thought form
realm, if an egregore,

00:06:10.070 --> 00:06:11.810 align:middle line:84%
classically
speaking, are thought

00:06:11.810 --> 00:06:14.880 align:middle line:84%
forms that we have collectively
rendered, so to speak,

00:06:14.880 --> 00:06:19.330 align:middle line:84%
or agreed upon
together, if an egregore

00:06:19.330 --> 00:06:21.080 align:middle line:84%
is the thought form
that's been reinforced

00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:23.630 align:middle line:84%
by multiple numbers
of people that

00:06:23.630 --> 00:06:26.430 align:middle line:84%
takes on a life of
its own, at what point

00:06:26.430 --> 00:06:33.250 align:middle line:84%
is that density so profound
that it creates an entity?

00:06:33.250 --> 00:06:35.600 align:middle line:84%
Does it just take the
repetition of something

00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:37.450 align:middle line:90%
through time to create this?

00:06:37.450 --> 00:06:39.830 align:middle line:84%
I want to give people
a visual understanding

00:06:39.830 --> 00:06:43.850 align:middle line:84%
of how we create these things
that we then become slaves to.

00:06:43.850 --> 00:06:46.190 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well,
it's very simple.

00:06:46.190 --> 00:06:48.924 align:middle line:90%
We get in love with our ideas.

00:06:48.924 --> 00:06:50.840 align:middle line:84%
We fall in love with our
ideas and our notions

00:06:50.840 --> 00:06:51.640 align:middle line:90%
and our creations.

00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And I think there's a
famous painting out there,

00:06:54.410 --> 00:06:57.750 align:middle line:84%
of course, the artist who falls
in love with his creation.

00:06:57.750 --> 00:06:58.550 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:06:58.550 --> 00:07:00.590 align:middle line:90%
So this is OK to some degree.

00:07:00.590 --> 00:07:02.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But we're
impassioning it.

00:07:02.240 --> 00:07:03.320 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: We're
impassioning it.

00:07:03.320 --> 00:07:04.850 align:middle line:84%
The difference is
when does it move

00:07:04.850 --> 00:07:08.480 align:middle line:84%
from being something which we
create and enliven into when

00:07:08.480 --> 00:07:09.955 align:middle line:90%
it influences us and dominates?

00:07:09.955 --> 00:07:11.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Its own
independent identity.

00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:13.320 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: It's own identity.

00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:16.150 align:middle line:84%
So we have to look at the
notion of the thought form.

00:07:16.150 --> 00:07:17.870 align:middle line:84%
All egregores are
thoughts forms.

00:07:17.870 --> 00:07:19.580 align:middle line:84%
But not all thought
forms are egregores.

00:07:19.580 --> 00:07:21.570 align:middle line:84%
Because the difference
is if we have an idea,

00:07:21.570 --> 00:07:23.611 align:middle line:84%
I have a goal in my life,
I want to write a book,

00:07:23.611 --> 00:07:26.270 align:middle line:84%
I want to have a show, I want
to run a successful business,

00:07:26.270 --> 00:07:29.850 align:middle line:84%
all of this involves all the
steps which you've discussed,

00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:30.856 align:middle line:90%
which you've outlined.

00:07:30.856 --> 00:07:33.230 align:middle line:84%
The difference is we have to
bring other people into that

00:07:33.230 --> 00:07:35.540 align:middle line:90%
to help make it happen often.

00:07:35.540 --> 00:07:38.720 align:middle line:84%
That is OK, a kind of an
egregore that we start.

00:07:38.720 --> 00:07:42.780 align:middle line:84%
The difference is that in most
of our day to day experiences,

00:07:42.780 --> 00:07:43.920 align:middle line:90%
these are not negative.

00:07:43.920 --> 00:07:44.720 align:middle line:90%
These are OK.

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:46.610 align:middle line:84%
We need them to
get through life.

00:07:46.610 --> 00:07:49.070 align:middle line:84%
But when we move into these
often very philosophical

00:07:49.070 --> 00:07:51.980 align:middle line:84%
and profound areas where
things can be very abstract,

00:07:51.980 --> 00:07:55.010 align:middle line:84%
particularly religion,
philosophy, and politics, where

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:58.310 align:middle line:84%
people can get so hung up on
an idea that they'll die for it

00:07:58.310 --> 00:08:02.420 align:middle line:84%
or kill for it,
that's when you know

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:03.990 align:middle line:84%
are you really sure
about this idea?

00:08:03.990 --> 00:08:07.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this is where it's
really fueled with emotion.

00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:08.930 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Emotion,
that's the key.

00:08:08.930 --> 00:08:11.270 align:middle line:84%
Because the entities,
and we're going

00:08:11.270 --> 00:08:13.400 align:middle line:84%
to talk about it from
the classical view,

00:08:13.400 --> 00:08:15.530 align:middle line:84%
there is a spiritual
entity at the other end

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:19.180 align:middle line:84%
of this that may or may not have
your best interests at heart.

00:08:19.180 --> 00:08:19.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:22.610 align:middle line:84%
Once the entity's been formed
and taken its own identity.

00:08:22.610 --> 00:08:23.865 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Well, not so--

00:08:23.865 --> 00:08:25.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or are you saying
actual other entities

00:08:25.100 --> 00:08:25.280 align:middle line:90%
in other realms?

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:26.705 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: There's others,
other entities in other realms.

00:08:26.705 --> 00:08:28.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That are taking
advantage of the egregore?

00:08:28.910 --> 00:08:31.340 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Because in
the classical world,

00:08:31.340 --> 00:08:35.419 align:middle line:84%
the priest craft would
create this conduit

00:08:35.419 --> 00:08:36.390 align:middle line:90%
to an intelligence.

00:08:36.390 --> 00:08:36.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:38.744 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: See, the
problem with human beings

00:08:38.744 --> 00:08:40.220 align:middle line:84%
is they're willfully
human centric.

00:08:40.220 --> 00:08:42.740 align:middle line:84%
We often think of the
cosmos only in terms of us.

00:08:42.740 --> 00:08:44.000 align:middle line:90%
Maybe we think of our pets.

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:45.710 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we think of
the animals we eat.

00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:49.070 align:middle line:84%
But we really don't give
much thought or consideration

00:08:49.070 --> 00:08:53.090 align:middle line:84%
to the host of invisible beings
that could exist in the cosmos.

00:08:53.090 --> 00:08:56.030 align:middle line:84%
And they may not all have
your best interests at heart,

00:08:56.030 --> 00:08:58.610 align:middle line:84%
just as not everyone walking
around on terra firma does.

00:08:58.610 --> 00:08:59.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:08:59.410 --> 00:09:01.070 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: We talk about
as above, so below.

00:09:01.070 --> 00:09:01.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:09:01.610 --> 00:09:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: But we
often don't really

00:09:02.630 --> 00:09:04.200 align:middle line:90%
think about what that means.

00:09:04.200 --> 00:09:06.680 align:middle line:84%
So the emotion is
the fuel of it all.

00:09:06.680 --> 00:09:09.050 align:middle line:84%
So when you find that your
emotions are running away

00:09:09.050 --> 00:09:11.570 align:middle line:84%
from you, that you don't
even understand where

00:09:11.570 --> 00:09:15.260 align:middle line:84%
these feelings are coming from,
and they're so impassioned,

00:09:15.260 --> 00:09:20.456 align:middle line:84%
that's when maybe this is the
tail's wagging the dog now.

00:09:20.456 --> 00:09:21.830 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you
would look at it

00:09:21.830 --> 00:09:25.490 align:middle line:84%
in a very extreme case, the
famous news footage of Hitler

00:09:25.490 --> 00:09:29.510 align:middle line:84%
standing in Nuremberg
in the stadium above all

00:09:29.510 --> 00:09:34.880 align:middle line:84%
of these people feeling them
into a frenzy, so to speak?

00:09:34.880 --> 00:09:35.930 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Very much so.

00:09:35.930 --> 00:09:37.471 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that
is an egregore that

00:09:37.471 --> 00:09:40.430 align:middle line:84%
has been created among
the people that is now

00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:44.450 align:middle line:84%
they are now hostage to on a
psychospiritual and emotional

00:09:44.450 --> 00:09:45.260 align:middle line:90%
level.

00:09:45.260 --> 00:09:47.570 align:middle line:84%
And you're saying that on
the other side of that,

00:09:47.570 --> 00:09:50.790 align:middle line:84%
that fuel that's
been created may

00:09:50.790 --> 00:09:54.800 align:middle line:84%
be being manipulated and
used by another force

00:09:54.800 --> 00:09:56.045 align:middle line:90%
for its own interests.

00:09:56.045 --> 00:09:58.544 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Correct, and that
would be the same with anything

00:09:58.544 --> 00:10:00.300 align:middle line:90%
that you see extremism involved.

00:10:00.300 --> 00:10:01.760 align:middle line:90%
I mean, communism's another one.

00:10:01.760 --> 00:10:03.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that bad
boy just won't die.

00:10:03.260 --> 00:10:04.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:10:04.060 --> 00:10:06.050 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And it's
constantly being reinvented

00:10:06.050 --> 00:10:07.530 align:middle line:90%
as if somehow it's OK.

00:10:07.530 --> 00:10:08.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:10:08.330 --> 00:10:09.170 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: You
see the same thing

00:10:09.170 --> 00:10:11.250 align:middle line:84%
with a lot of sporting events
when they just break out

00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:12.195 align:middle line:90%
into this kind of hostility.

00:10:12.195 --> 00:10:13.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, no, this is true.

00:10:13.520 --> 00:10:15.936 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I don't think I've
ever been as frightened as when

00:10:15.936 --> 00:10:18.810 align:middle line:84%
I was at a Texas OU game
sitting in the bleachers

00:10:18.810 --> 00:10:21.570 align:middle line:84%
with 100,000 people
stomping their feet.

00:10:21.570 --> 00:10:24.660 align:middle line:84%
I literally wanted to get out
of there because that thing was

00:10:24.660 --> 00:10:25.960 align:middle line:90%
dangerous.

00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:27.000 align:middle line:90%
It would take over.

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:28.110 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, and
you look at it now

00:10:28.110 --> 00:10:28.980 align:middle line:90%
and then there are other kinds.

00:10:28.980 --> 00:10:29.820 align:middle line:90%
These are easy to see.

00:10:29.820 --> 00:10:31.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is
why we're talking about

00:10:31.260 --> 00:10:32.370 align:middle line:90%
because they are extreme.

00:10:32.370 --> 00:10:33.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:10:33.170 --> 00:10:35.945 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And that's really
important to point out.

00:10:35.945 --> 00:10:38.070 align:middle line:84%
The examples I give in the
book, the examples we're

00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:40.760 align:middle line:84%
talking about here, we're
using very black and white ones

00:10:40.760 --> 00:10:42.990 align:middle line:84%
so that we can begin
to set a framework up

00:10:42.990 --> 00:10:44.995 align:middle line:84%
for internal reflection
on our relationships.

00:10:44.995 --> 00:10:46.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:48.150 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: But they can often
be more subtle or insidious.

00:10:48.150 --> 00:10:48.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:51.750 align:middle line:84%
So we get a picture of the
really dense gross ones.

00:10:51.750 --> 00:10:54.000 align:middle line:84%
So let's get into
some definitions

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:56.520 align:middle line:84%
that different people,
different ways in which this

00:10:56.520 --> 00:10:57.909 align:middle line:90%
was described in your book.

00:10:57.909 --> 00:11:00.450 align:middle line:84%
Should I just pop through a few
and then you comment on them?

00:11:00.450 --> 00:11:00.780 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Whatever you want.

00:11:00.780 --> 00:11:01.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:11:01.580 --> 00:11:04.980 align:middle line:84%
Psyche and physical embodiment
of ideologies and systems.

00:11:04.980 --> 00:11:06.660 align:middle line:84%
That seems self
explanatory, right?

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:07.460 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Yes.

00:11:07.460 --> 00:11:10.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Energy complex as
living beings that must be fed

00:11:10.080 --> 00:11:11.040 align:middle line:90%
and nurtured.

00:11:11.040 --> 00:11:13.530 align:middle line:84%
Now that part we need to
get into a little bit.

00:11:13.530 --> 00:11:15.420 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to go
further into it later.

00:11:15.420 --> 00:11:16.880 align:middle line:90%
Fed and nurtured?

00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:19.294 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well,
for your viewers,

00:11:19.294 --> 00:11:21.210 align:middle line:84%
most of them are involved,
if not all of them,

00:11:21.210 --> 00:11:23.730 align:middle line:84%
in some kind of
spiritual practice.

00:11:23.730 --> 00:11:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Often, these spiritual
practices can

00:11:25.440 --> 00:11:30.210 align:middle line:84%
involve some kind of ideation,
idealizing, I should say,

00:11:30.210 --> 00:11:36.360 align:middle line:84%
idealizing of a person or of an
entity, a god form of some kind

00:11:36.360 --> 00:11:37.440 align:middle line:90%
or deity.

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:41.250 align:middle line:84%
We see this throughout Hinduism,
Buddhism, Tibetan Buddhism.

00:11:41.250 --> 00:11:44.790 align:middle line:84%
We see this in the
classical mythologies.

00:11:44.790 --> 00:11:47.100 align:middle line:84%
And there is a form of
worship or devotion.

00:11:47.100 --> 00:11:48.320 align:middle line:90%
Devotion is the key.

00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:50.746 align:middle line:84%
We're all constantly told
devotion, devotion, devotion,

00:11:50.746 --> 00:11:52.620 align:middle line:84%
even to the teacher,
devotion to the teacher.

00:11:52.620 --> 00:11:53.850 align:middle line:90%
And what is devotion?

00:11:53.850 --> 00:11:59.160 align:middle line:84%
But it is a heartfelt
opening or receptivity

00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:04.110 align:middle line:84%
to what they have to offer
you, but it's emotional.

00:12:04.110 --> 00:12:05.970 align:middle line:90%
It is not intellectual.

00:12:05.970 --> 00:12:06.960 align:middle line:90%
It is not analytical.

00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:09.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you're often
told, don't analyze this.

00:12:09.840 --> 00:12:11.355 align:middle line:90%
Don't think about this.

00:12:11.355 --> 00:12:13.230 align:middle line:84%
Now sometimes, it even
goes so far as to say,

00:12:13.230 --> 00:12:17.190 align:middle line:84%
don't even criticize it,
well, maybe not at the time.

00:12:17.190 --> 00:12:18.780 align:middle line:84%
Afterwards, maybe
some will encourage

00:12:18.780 --> 00:12:19.696 align:middle line:90%
you to think about it.

00:12:19.696 --> 00:12:22.560 align:middle line:84%
But it's that emotionalism
that is the hook because it

00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:25.080 align:middle line:90%
can feel so wonderful.

00:12:25.080 --> 00:12:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And anyone who's been to a
revival meeting or some kind

00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:33.270 align:middle line:84%
of even in an NA or AA
meeting where people

00:12:33.270 --> 00:12:35.640 align:middle line:84%
are telling their
heartfelt stories,

00:12:35.640 --> 00:12:37.854 align:middle line:90%
you can just feel that emotion.

00:12:37.854 --> 00:12:39.270 align:middle line:84%
How many times
have people watched

00:12:39.270 --> 00:12:40.410 align:middle line:90%
a movie and they begin to cry?

00:12:40.410 --> 00:12:41.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right/

00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:42.790 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: How many
people watched a movie

00:12:42.790 --> 00:12:46.350 align:middle line:84%
and they begin to feel sorrow
or sadness or happiness and joy?

00:12:46.350 --> 00:12:49.500 align:middle line:84%
We're far more easily
emotionally manipulated

00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:51.474 align:middle line:90%
than we tend to believe.

00:12:51.474 --> 00:12:53.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that's
how it's feeding us.

00:12:53.140 --> 00:12:56.190 align:middle line:84%
Now how are those emotions
then feeding and pumping up

00:12:56.190 --> 00:12:57.510 align:middle line:90%
the strength of the egregore?

00:12:57.510 --> 00:12:59.464 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: It's a relationship.

00:12:59.464 --> 00:13:00.380 align:middle line:90%
It's a two way street.

00:13:00.380 --> 00:13:00.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's a
self-feeding loop.

00:13:00.670 --> 00:13:01.430 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: It's a
self-feeding loop.

00:13:01.430 --> 00:13:02.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:13:02.050 --> 00:13:04.260 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Now the thing
is they often have to grow.

00:13:04.260 --> 00:13:06.760 align:middle line:84%
That's why you see the
idealism is the emphasis.

00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:08.010 align:middle line:90%
We're going to save the world.

00:13:08.010 --> 00:13:10.176 align:middle line:84%
We're going to make the
better world a better place.

00:13:10.176 --> 00:13:13.100 align:middle line:84%
We're going to turn
it into utopia.

00:13:13.100 --> 00:13:14.830 align:middle line:84%
But that means what
do we have to do?

00:13:14.830 --> 00:13:16.830 align:middle line:90%
We got to spread the word.

00:13:16.830 --> 00:13:18.810 align:middle line:84%
We've got to
recruit more people.

00:13:18.810 --> 00:13:21.357 align:middle line:84%
We've got to absorb more
people into the movement.

00:13:21.357 --> 00:13:23.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm, more
emotion, more energy.

00:13:23.190 --> 00:13:25.000 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: More emotion,
more energy, more feeding.

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:26.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
again, the X factor

00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:29.335 align:middle line:84%
is you don't know what's on
the other side of the egregore.

00:13:29.335 --> 00:13:30.210 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: You don't.

00:13:30.210 --> 00:13:34.800 align:middle line:84%
And this is where you
have to ask yourself

00:13:34.800 --> 00:13:36.240 align:middle line:90%
the question again and again.

00:13:36.240 --> 00:13:38.520 align:middle line:84%
I'll say it throughout
the interview.

00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:40.750 align:middle line:84%
Am I getting out of this
what I was promised?

00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:41.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:13:41.900 --> 00:13:44.790 align:middle line:90%
OK, another one here.

00:13:44.790 --> 00:13:49.350 align:middle line:84%
Is group consciousness
formed by serious initiates?

00:13:49.350 --> 00:13:51.850 align:middle line:84%
Now you touched on this
a little while ago,

00:13:51.850 --> 00:13:55.050 align:middle line:84%
where you have initiates
of various faiths, which

00:13:55.050 --> 00:14:00.390 align:middle line:84%
intentionally come together
to create this commonly

00:14:00.390 --> 00:14:03.720 align:middle line:84%
held belief or this
egregore to reach

00:14:03.720 --> 00:14:07.440 align:middle line:90%
into other realms of entities.

00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:09.415 align:middle line:90%
Talk about that a little bit.

00:14:09.415 --> 00:14:11.790 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, again, as we
saw in the classical period

00:14:11.790 --> 00:14:14.340 align:middle line:84%
where the priesthood
would intentionally

00:14:14.340 --> 00:14:18.150 align:middle line:84%
create these rituals and
actions and forms of worship

00:14:18.150 --> 00:14:20.040 align:middle line:84%
to make contact
and communication

00:14:20.040 --> 00:14:22.050 align:middle line:84%
with the invisible realms,
we see the same thing

00:14:22.050 --> 00:14:24.870 align:middle line:84%
going on today in a variety
of organizations and movements

00:14:24.870 --> 00:14:26.020 align:middle line:90%
intentionally.

00:14:26.020 --> 00:14:29.250 align:middle line:84%
And some of them are actively
involved in religion or cultism

00:14:29.250 --> 00:14:30.340 align:middle line:90%
or metaphysics.

00:14:30.340 --> 00:14:33.210 align:middle line:84%
And again, these can be
with very good intentions,

00:14:33.210 --> 00:14:35.005 align:middle line:84%
and at times, can have
very good results.

00:14:35.005 --> 00:14:37.067 align:middle line:90%
I want to be clear on that.

00:14:37.067 --> 00:14:38.650 align:middle line:84%
But because these
are living entities,

00:14:38.650 --> 00:14:40.620 align:middle line:90%
they have a life cycle.

00:14:40.620 --> 00:14:44.040 align:middle line:84%
And just as people
and organizations

00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:48.490 align:middle line:84%
have a beginning, a middle, a
decline, and possibly an end,

00:14:48.490 --> 00:14:52.350 align:middle line:84%
so can these psychic
entities, these egregores.

00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:56.040 align:middle line:84%
And when they go toxic, when
they're not getting fed,

00:14:56.040 --> 00:14:57.720 align:middle line:84%
or when they're in
the state of decay,

00:14:57.720 --> 00:14:59.720 align:middle line:84%
that's when they become
the most dangerous to us

00:14:59.720 --> 00:15:02.670 align:middle line:84%
spiritually because that's
when people become dogmatic.

00:15:02.670 --> 00:15:04.915 align:middle line:84%
They become extremely
dogmatic on the view.

00:15:04.915 --> 00:15:05.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Entrenched.

00:15:05.790 --> 00:15:08.335 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Entrenched, yes.

00:15:08.335 --> 00:15:10.710 align:middle line:84%
And you can see that because
people are no longer working

00:15:10.710 --> 00:15:12.580 align:middle line:90%
from experience.

00:15:12.580 --> 00:15:15.330 align:middle line:84%
They're working from,
we'll say, the written word

00:15:15.330 --> 00:15:18.567 align:middle line:84%
or what they were told, but
not from personal experience.

00:15:18.567 --> 00:15:20.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So now this is
creating a divisiveness--

00:15:20.650 --> 00:15:21.160 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Yes.

00:15:21.160 --> 00:15:22.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --whenever
there is that dogmatism.

00:15:22.900 --> 00:15:24.983 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Because your
spirituality should always

00:15:24.983 --> 00:15:28.480 align:middle line:84%
ultimately be about your
individual experience

00:15:28.480 --> 00:15:30.700 align:middle line:84%
and how you can come to
understand that clearly

00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:33.490 align:middle line:84%
and precisely and
usefully in your life.

00:15:33.490 --> 00:15:36.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk about
when they go super toxic.

00:15:36.610 --> 00:15:39.340 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
groups that are more

00:15:39.340 --> 00:15:43.000 align:middle line:84%
oriented toward the dark
side, blood sacrifice,

00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:43.930 align:middle line:90%
so on and so forth.

00:15:43.930 --> 00:15:45.880 align:middle line:84%
Throughout history,
it's been very common.

00:15:45.880 --> 00:15:47.960 align:middle line:90%
It still happens today.

00:15:47.960 --> 00:15:50.830 align:middle line:84%
So what did you learn
in your research

00:15:50.830 --> 00:15:53.650 align:middle line:84%
when the intention
is dark to begin with

00:15:53.650 --> 00:15:56.320 align:middle line:84%
and you create a very,
very dark egregore,

00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:59.110 align:middle line:84%
and then what can happen
on the other side of it?

00:15:59.110 --> 00:16:01.070 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, nothing
good comes of this.

00:16:01.070 --> 00:16:01.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:16:01.410 --> 00:16:02.993 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: I mean,
this is the problem

00:16:02.993 --> 00:16:06.760 align:middle line:84%
and because the beginning is
always very selfish, always.

00:16:06.760 --> 00:16:07.844 align:middle line:90%
It's always just about me.

00:16:07.844 --> 00:16:09.593 align:middle line:84%
Even if you're involved
with other people,

00:16:09.593 --> 00:16:11.200 align:middle line:84%
ultimately, it's
really you're just

00:16:11.200 --> 00:16:13.300 align:middle line:84%
involved with it because of
what you hope to get out of it.

00:16:13.300 --> 00:16:14.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Power, usually power.

00:16:14.710 --> 00:16:16.210 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: It's
almost always power.

00:16:16.210 --> 00:16:18.760 align:middle line:84%
And the toxicity of
power, the power complex,

00:16:18.760 --> 00:16:21.490 align:middle line:84%
which is an article that was
recently posted on my blog

00:16:21.490 --> 00:16:24.779 align:middle line:84%
by a guest author who is
a Jungian psychoanalyst,

00:16:24.779 --> 00:16:26.320 align:middle line:84%
really talks about
that is that power

00:16:26.320 --> 00:16:27.861 align:middle line:84%
complex we see in
all of these groups

00:16:27.861 --> 00:16:31.780 align:middle line:84%
both supposedly geared towards
the light and those not.

00:16:31.780 --> 00:16:35.090 align:middle line:84%
But when you're involved in
the life force, of course,

00:16:35.090 --> 00:16:36.880 align:middle line:84%
as we hear it's
getting near Halloween,

00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:39.700 align:middle line:84%
and Dracula always said,
the life is in the blood,

00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:41.770 align:middle line:84%
but that is true because
that is the carrier

00:16:41.770 --> 00:16:45.130 align:middle line:84%
of the psychic energies,
the prana or the qi.

00:16:45.130 --> 00:16:47.980 align:middle line:84%
And when that is
concentrated and released,

00:16:47.980 --> 00:16:51.150 align:middle line:84%
the belief is, among
various esoteric groups,

00:16:51.150 --> 00:16:53.770 align:middle line:84%
that is how you can grab
that, you can manipulate it,

00:16:53.770 --> 00:16:58.000 align:middle line:84%
and you can direct it to feed
whatever spiritual entity

00:16:58.000 --> 00:16:59.605 align:middle line:90%
you're dedicating it to.

00:16:59.605 --> 00:17:01.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's really very
important because that

00:17:01.480 --> 00:17:04.720 align:middle line:84%
is the function of the purpose
of these ancient sacrifices

00:17:04.720 --> 00:17:07.390 align:middle line:84%
or even if they
are going on today.

00:17:07.390 --> 00:17:11.500 align:middle line:84%
The problem is
that it is already

00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:15.700 align:middle line:84%
started from such a negative
and selfish perspective

00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:18.160 align:middle line:84%
that the people
involved, ultimately,

00:17:18.160 --> 00:17:21.430 align:middle line:84%
are going to come
to no good end.

00:17:21.430 --> 00:17:23.290 align:middle line:84%
Just nothing good
can come from it.

00:17:23.290 --> 00:17:26.060 align:middle line:84%
I think maybe what
is related to this,

00:17:26.060 --> 00:17:29.190 align:middle line:84%
though, is when healthy
aggregates go toxic.

00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:29.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:17:29.990 --> 00:17:31.989 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And we talked
about that in the book.

00:17:31.989 --> 00:17:35.110 align:middle line:84%
We gave an example, very extreme
example, again, very extreme

00:17:35.110 --> 00:17:37.990 align:middle line:84%
just so that people
would see worst case

00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:40.630 align:middle line:84%
scenario, in which
folks were involved

00:17:40.630 --> 00:17:44.170 align:middle line:90%
in a well-known esoteric order.

00:17:44.170 --> 00:17:46.390 align:middle line:84%
And most of the
leadership ended up

00:17:46.390 --> 00:17:48.040 align:middle line:84%
coming down with
the commonalities

00:17:48.040 --> 00:17:50.740 align:middle line:84%
of blood diseases, all
very rare diseases.

00:17:50.740 --> 00:17:51.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:17:51.730 --> 00:17:53.860 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: It wasn't, oh,
this one got pneumonia,

00:17:53.860 --> 00:17:56.710 align:middle line:84%
or this one got
whatever, the flu.

00:17:56.710 --> 00:18:00.860 align:middle line:84%
It's all with the same kind
of strange, peculiar blood

00:18:00.860 --> 00:18:01.660 align:middle line:90%
disorders.

00:18:01.660 --> 00:18:02.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:05.290 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So one
of the physicians

00:18:05.290 --> 00:18:07.690 align:middle line:84%
who was involved with the
group talked to me about this

00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:11.470 align:middle line:90%
and said, these are oddities.

00:18:11.470 --> 00:18:13.884 align:middle line:90%
These are outliers, anomalies.

00:18:13.884 --> 00:18:16.300 align:middle line:84%
Why so we have so many of them
concentrated in this group?

00:18:16.300 --> 00:18:18.220 align:middle line:90%
What do they all have in common?

00:18:18.220 --> 00:18:20.110 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, that
group in particular

00:18:20.110 --> 00:18:23.710 align:middle line:84%
placed a great deal of emphasis
on the notion of the egregore.

00:18:23.710 --> 00:18:25.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:18:25.690 --> 00:18:29.140 align:middle line:84%
OK, and the egregore can be
even, for example, Horace,

00:18:29.140 --> 00:18:31.720 align:middle line:84%
Jesus, Muhammad, all the
masters of influence, right?

00:18:31.720 --> 00:18:32.520 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Sure.

00:18:32.520 --> 00:18:33.519 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Buddha, right?

00:18:33.519 --> 00:18:36.220 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: They are because
you see that happening today.

00:18:36.220 --> 00:18:40.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Jacques Valei
said it quite accurately.

00:18:40.100 --> 00:18:44.320 align:middle line:84%
We're involved in the bloody
brutal for celebrity status

00:18:44.320 --> 00:18:47.890 align:middle line:84%
in order to get our message out
there and to be listened to.

00:18:47.890 --> 00:18:52.150 align:middle line:84%
And when you do this,
there's an apotheosis

00:18:52.150 --> 00:18:55.870 align:middle line:84%
that takes place, the
elevation to divine being.

00:18:55.870 --> 00:18:58.480 align:middle line:84%
We see that in the rotunda
of the Capitol building

00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:00.917 align:middle line:84%
where George
Washington is elevated.

00:19:00.917 --> 00:19:02.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, he's
elevated to deity.

00:19:02.500 --> 00:19:04.700 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: To deity status.

00:19:04.700 --> 00:19:08.800 align:middle line:84%
And we see it, I mean, go to
any college campus in September,

00:19:08.800 --> 00:19:12.070 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to see posters
of Marilyn Monroe, James

00:19:12.070 --> 00:19:12.870 align:middle line:90%
Dean, Che--

00:19:12.870 --> 00:19:14.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, come on, it's
been quite a while

00:19:14.590 --> 00:19:16.240 align:middle line:84%
since these folks
have been alive.

00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:18.800 align:middle line:84%
Yet, we continue to elevate
them to this status.

00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:19.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:20.400 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Why?

00:19:20.400 --> 00:19:21.970 align:middle line:84%
Because we see them
as an embodiment

00:19:21.970 --> 00:19:25.100 align:middle line:84%
of the classical
symbolism of Venus.

00:19:25.100 --> 00:19:25.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:19:25.900 --> 00:19:27.820 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Marilyn Monroe
was Venus incarnate.

00:19:27.820 --> 00:19:31.390 align:middle line:90%
James Dean, he's the bad boy.

00:19:31.390 --> 00:19:33.290 align:middle line:90%
Where does he fit in there?

00:19:33.290 --> 00:19:34.090 align:middle line:90%
He's not quite--

00:19:34.090 --> 00:19:36.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He's sensitive
and misunderstood.

00:19:36.130 --> 00:19:39.460 align:middle line:84%
And he runs afoul of
everybody as a result of it.

00:19:39.460 --> 00:19:43.110 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So there's a Greek
god that he personifies,

00:19:43.110 --> 00:19:45.280 align:middle line:84%
and that's really
important to notice.

00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:47.680 align:middle line:84%
That we as people, and we
talk, as above, so below,

00:19:47.680 --> 00:19:50.410 align:middle line:84%
and we talk about our charts
and astrology, but each of us

00:19:50.410 --> 00:19:53.315 align:middle line:84%
has aspects of planetary
energies or deities--

00:19:53.315 --> 00:19:54.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:19:54.190 --> 00:19:55.360 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: --that we embody.

00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:57.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:19:57.010 --> 00:19:58.720 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: We're very mercurial.

00:19:58.720 --> 00:19:59.020 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:19:59.020 --> 00:20:00.680 align:middle line:84%
Because we're talking
and communicating

00:20:00.680 --> 00:20:01.780 align:middle line:90%
and all of this stuff.

00:20:01.780 --> 00:20:03.555 align:middle line:84%
Just so your listeners
can be watching,

00:20:03.555 --> 00:20:06.165 align:middle line:84%
your viewers can begin to
think about it in themselves.

00:20:06.165 --> 00:20:08.290 align:middle line:84%
But then you take someone
like Che Guevara, I mean,

00:20:08.290 --> 00:20:10.330 align:middle line:90%
he was Castro's assassin.

00:20:10.330 --> 00:20:11.340 align:middle line:90%
He was a murderer.

00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:15.375 align:middle line:84%
And yet, we sell posters
of him in college campuses

00:20:15.375 --> 00:20:16.200 align:middle line:90%
as if he's a hero.

00:20:16.200 --> 00:20:16.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, he's idolized.

00:20:16.690 --> 00:20:18.250 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:20:18.250 --> 00:20:19.450 align:middle line:90%
What about corporations?

00:20:19.450 --> 00:20:21.533 align:middle line:84%
Because it seems like one
of the biggest egregores

00:20:21.533 --> 00:20:23.207 align:middle line:90%
would be corporate--

00:20:23.207 --> 00:20:24.040 align:middle line:90%
what do you call it?

00:20:24.040 --> 00:20:24.840 align:middle line:90%
Culture?

00:20:24.840 --> 00:20:26.680 align:middle line:84%
Now they call it
corporate culture.

00:20:26.680 --> 00:20:28.310 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yes, corporate
culture is the biggest one.

00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:29.810 align:middle line:84%
Well, two of them,
corporate culture

00:20:29.810 --> 00:20:30.940 align:middle line:90%
and political correctness.

00:20:30.940 --> 00:20:31.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:20:31.740 --> 00:20:34.030 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: These are the
two biggest egregores today.

00:20:34.030 --> 00:20:38.800 align:middle line:84%
And they intersect through the
priesthood of the department

00:20:38.800 --> 00:20:41.200 align:middle line:90%
of human resources.

00:20:41.200 --> 00:20:43.040 align:middle line:90%
That's where they come together.

00:20:43.040 --> 00:20:46.480 align:middle line:84%
So when we look at
a corporate culture,

00:20:46.480 --> 00:20:48.940 align:middle line:84%
it is an egregore
that you voluntarily

00:20:48.940 --> 00:20:51.070 align:middle line:90%
agree to participate in.

00:20:51.070 --> 00:20:52.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:20:52.420 --> 00:20:54.700 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting,
because there

00:20:54.700 --> 00:20:58.660 align:middle line:84%
are have been experimental
corporate cultures,

00:20:58.660 --> 00:21:02.050 align:middle line:84%
and there have been more
democratic corporate cultures

00:21:02.050 --> 00:21:04.270 align:middle line:84%
that do come along
from time to time,

00:21:04.270 --> 00:21:09.040 align:middle line:84%
where the employees are even
the primary shareholders.

00:21:09.040 --> 00:21:12.260 align:middle line:84%
And there you see, and this
I'm getting into for a reason,

00:21:12.260 --> 00:21:15.130 align:middle line:84%
it's just as with
religions and gods.

00:21:15.130 --> 00:21:17.230 align:middle line:84%
And I have it written
down this way,

00:21:17.230 --> 00:21:19.240 align:middle line:84%
you have certain
corporate egregores

00:21:19.240 --> 00:21:21.490 align:middle line:90%
where you obey and you worship.

00:21:21.490 --> 00:21:22.900 align:middle line:84%
And you have others
where there's

00:21:22.900 --> 00:21:25.680 align:middle line:90%
appreciation and gratitude.

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:30.100 align:middle line:84%
Same, it's offering
something, but distinctly

00:21:30.100 --> 00:21:34.000 align:middle line:84%
different in its intention,
how it's taken up and received,

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:36.650 align:middle line:84%
and the comfort of the person
on the giving end of it.

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:37.450 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Yes.

00:21:37.450 --> 00:21:40.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so in most
corporations, it's top down.

00:21:40.310 --> 00:21:41.110 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Mm-hmm.

00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:41.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right?

00:21:41.620 --> 00:21:42.640 align:middle line:90%
Boom.

00:21:42.640 --> 00:21:44.530 align:middle line:90%
And that's worship and obey.

00:21:44.530 --> 00:21:47.960 align:middle line:84%
That's like almost like
lower gods, lower religions,

00:21:47.960 --> 00:21:48.860 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:21:48.860 --> 00:21:52.860 align:middle line:84%
And that dominates
most of our planet,

00:21:52.860 --> 00:21:57.670 align:middle line:84%
not even to get into the
notion of political structures.

00:21:57.670 --> 00:22:00.220 align:middle line:84%
But people who are plugged
in through corporate systems

00:22:00.220 --> 00:22:03.460 align:middle line:84%
and then their sheer extension
through mass media, which

00:22:03.460 --> 00:22:06.940 align:middle line:84%
is the next one we'll get
into, to influence our thinking

00:22:06.940 --> 00:22:10.510 align:middle line:84%
and manipulate us into buying
their product and so forth

00:22:10.510 --> 00:22:13.990 align:middle line:84%
is very much a hierarchical
top down structure

00:22:13.990 --> 00:22:15.220 align:middle line:90%
the majority of the time.

00:22:15.220 --> 00:22:17.110 align:middle line:90%
And we're just used to it.

00:22:17.110 --> 00:22:21.070 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, to really
look at this carefully,

00:22:21.070 --> 00:22:24.710 align:middle line:84%
we like to think that
magic has gone away.

00:22:24.710 --> 00:22:27.290 align:middle line:84%
However, Ioan
Couliano in his book,

00:22:27.290 --> 00:22:29.600 align:middle line:84%
"Eros and Magic in
the Renaissance,"

00:22:29.600 --> 00:22:32.650 align:middle line:84%
described very carefully
the survival of magic

00:22:32.650 --> 00:22:36.070 align:middle line:84%
particularly through
corporate industrial complexes

00:22:36.070 --> 00:22:37.390 align:middle line:90%
and government complexes.

00:22:37.390 --> 00:22:39.800 align:middle line:84%
And having come from
communist Romania,

00:22:39.800 --> 00:22:44.890 align:middle line:84%
he was quite aware of the role
of social control mechanisms,

00:22:44.890 --> 00:22:48.340 align:middle line:84%
media and corporate
combinations to keep people

00:22:48.340 --> 00:22:51.310 align:middle line:84%
thinking and acting
on particular lines.

00:22:51.310 --> 00:22:53.845 align:middle line:84%
And his book is really something
that everyone should read.

00:22:53.845 --> 00:22:55.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Tell us
his name again.

00:22:55.220 --> 00:22:56.053 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Couliano.

00:22:56.053 --> 00:22:58.170 align:middle line:84%
The book is "Eros and
Magic in the Renaissance."

00:22:58.170 --> 00:22:58.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:22:58.970 --> 00:23:01.190 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: The University
of Chicago Press.

00:23:01.190 --> 00:23:01.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:23:01.990 --> 00:23:03.781 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And of
course, he focuses mostly

00:23:03.781 --> 00:23:07.570 align:middle line:84%
on the writings
of Giordano Bruno.

00:23:07.570 --> 00:23:12.670 align:middle line:84%
And Bruno's book, "On
the Bonds in General,"

00:23:12.670 --> 00:23:14.860 align:middle line:84%
it's kind of a
boring title, but it

00:23:14.860 --> 00:23:17.980 align:middle line:84%
was written nine years
before he was executed,

00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:21.670 align:middle line:84%
burned at the stake in
1600 in the center of Rome.

00:23:21.670 --> 00:23:25.090 align:middle line:84%
And that book in
particular is probably

00:23:25.090 --> 00:23:29.060 align:middle line:84%
more important than
Machiavelli's "The Prince,"

00:23:29.060 --> 00:23:31.540 align:middle line:84%
because "The Prince"
talks about power

00:23:31.540 --> 00:23:35.350 align:middle line:84%
in terms of very conventional
ways of acquiring it.

00:23:35.350 --> 00:23:38.830 align:middle line:84%
But Bruno's book talks
about in terms of,

00:23:38.830 --> 00:23:40.720 align:middle line:90%
what is the role of influence?

00:23:40.720 --> 00:23:42.970 align:middle line:84%
How do we influence
the individual?

00:23:42.970 --> 00:23:45.280 align:middle line:84%
And how do we
influence the masses?

00:23:45.280 --> 00:23:49.110 align:middle line:84%
And how we do that through
symbols and signs and images?

00:23:49.110 --> 00:23:53.170 align:middle line:84%
The power of the image,
the power of the brand,

00:23:53.170 --> 00:23:58.572 align:middle line:84%
the power of the logo, the
power of the slogan or mantra,

00:23:58.572 --> 00:24:02.410 align:middle line:84%
the spell, the enchantment
that takes place

00:24:02.410 --> 00:24:06.700 align:middle line:84%
through constant repetition
and exposure to these things.

00:24:06.700 --> 00:24:08.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Add music
to it, which goes

00:24:08.410 --> 00:24:12.340 align:middle line:84%
deep into the emotional
aspect of being to boost it

00:24:12.340 --> 00:24:15.640 align:middle line:84%
and the repetition of the slogan
with the music repeatedly,

00:24:15.640 --> 00:24:17.980 align:middle line:84%
for example, and you have
something hardwired enough

00:24:17.980 --> 00:24:20.141 align:middle line:84%
you'll remember it
on your deathbed.

00:24:20.141 --> 00:24:22.390 align:middle line:84%
I still know all the jingles
from the various products

00:24:22.390 --> 00:24:23.760 align:middle line:90%
in my childhood.

00:24:23.760 --> 00:24:24.480 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: I was just
going to say that.

00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:25.860 align:middle line:84%
How often have you
found yourself,

00:24:25.860 --> 00:24:27.260 align:middle line:84%
you're doing your dishes,
you're doing something,

00:24:27.260 --> 00:24:28.500 align:middle line:90%
and some song's in your--

00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:28.580 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:24:28.580 --> 00:24:30.871 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: (SINGING) --good
at dirt and grime and grease

00:24:30.871 --> 00:24:32.640 align:middle line:90%
and just--

00:24:32.640 --> 00:24:33.440 align:middle line:90%
No, it's true.

00:24:33.440 --> 00:24:35.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we think,
oh, a lot of people

00:24:35.340 --> 00:24:37.090 align:middle line:84%
say, well, I don't
work for a corporation.

00:24:37.090 --> 00:24:39.220 align:middle line:84%
I got out of the corporate
life a long time ago,

00:24:39.220 --> 00:24:41.750 align:middle line:90%
and no more top down with me.

00:24:41.750 --> 00:24:45.130 align:middle line:84%
However, we are succumbing to
it with these subtle messagings

00:24:45.130 --> 00:24:48.100 align:middle line:84%
if we are dialed in
at all to, I think,

00:24:48.100 --> 00:24:51.140 align:middle line:84%
mass media and the
messaging systems around us.

00:24:51.140 --> 00:24:55.810 align:middle line:84%
It takes an incredible
amount of personal definition

00:24:55.810 --> 00:24:59.680 align:middle line:84%
and will to be able to live
beyond these egregoric messages

00:24:59.680 --> 00:25:01.947 align:middle line:90%
coming through to us constantly.

00:25:01.947 --> 00:25:03.530 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: It's
increasingly difficult

00:25:03.530 --> 00:25:06.100 align:middle line:84%
and because of the
degree to which we're

00:25:06.100 --> 00:25:07.900 align:middle line:90%
wired in all the time.

00:25:07.900 --> 00:25:10.210 align:middle line:84%
People really do
need to disconnect

00:25:10.210 --> 00:25:11.587 align:middle line:90%
and be very selective.

00:25:11.587 --> 00:25:13.420 align:middle line:84%
Now we don't want to
create an echo chamber.

00:25:13.420 --> 00:25:15.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's just
an egregore of itself.

00:25:15.220 --> 00:25:16.912 align:middle line:84%
That's another social
control mechanism.

00:25:16.912 --> 00:25:19.370 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to create an
echo chamber where all you hear

00:25:19.370 --> 00:25:20.930 align:middle line:90%
is what you want to hear.

00:25:20.930 --> 00:25:23.030 align:middle line:84%
But you do have to be
selective and limit

00:25:23.030 --> 00:25:25.280 align:middle line:84%
the amount of
exposure that you have

00:25:25.280 --> 00:25:27.641 align:middle line:84%
to media and particular
types of media

00:25:27.641 --> 00:25:29.390 align:middle line:84%
and begin to analyze
the media that you're

00:25:29.390 --> 00:25:31.260 align:middle line:90%
exposed to more carefully.

00:25:31.260 --> 00:25:35.900 align:middle line:84%
Because again, this topic has
two areas of consideration.

00:25:35.900 --> 00:25:38.600 align:middle line:84%
One is what we think of
as general mass media

00:25:38.600 --> 00:25:41.520 align:middle line:84%
and mass psychology, and
that's very important.

00:25:41.520 --> 00:25:43.490 align:middle line:84%
There's been a tremendous
amount of information

00:25:43.490 --> 00:25:47.390 align:middle line:84%
written about that even
in the '50s and '60s.

00:25:47.390 --> 00:25:48.890 align:middle line:84%
But then we move
beyond that into

00:25:48.890 --> 00:25:51.930 align:middle line:84%
the psychospiritual aspect,
the metaphysical aspect.

00:25:51.930 --> 00:25:53.780 align:middle line:84%
And that's saying
these things just

00:25:53.780 --> 00:25:55.140 align:middle line:90%
don't end with our brain pans.

00:25:55.140 --> 00:25:57.230 align:middle line:84%
They just don't end
with our thoughts.

00:25:57.230 --> 00:26:01.710 align:middle line:84%
We are connected to some kind
of psychic or emotional force

00:26:01.710 --> 00:26:02.510 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:26:02.510 --> 00:26:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And we have to know
