00:30:09.440 --> 00:30:11.690 align:middle line:84%
No matter what you say
about her, I don't care.

00:30:11.690 --> 00:30:13.787 align:middle line:84%
She's just a phenomenal
story of a person to read.

00:30:13.787 --> 00:30:16.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Are you talking about
Alexandra or Madame Blavatsky?

00:30:16.370 --> 00:30:17.040 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Both of them.

00:30:17.040 --> 00:30:18.206 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with that.

00:30:18.206 --> 00:30:20.882 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a wild character
definitely, hugely conflicted

00:30:20.882 --> 00:30:23.090 align:middle line:84%
in a lot of areas, but there
are a lot of brilliance.

00:30:23.090 --> 00:30:23.870 align:middle line:90%
Alexandra?

00:30:23.870 --> 00:30:24.440 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: David-Neel.

00:30:24.440 --> 00:30:25.356 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: David, yeah.

00:30:25.356 --> 00:30:30.230 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And she was in
Tibet in the '20s and '30s.

00:30:30.230 --> 00:30:34.220 align:middle line:84%
And she helped bring
Tibetan Buddhism to the West

00:30:34.220 --> 00:30:36.770 align:middle line:90%
in many ways.

00:30:36.770 --> 00:30:39.260 align:middle line:10%
And she wrote in her book,
"Magic and Mystery in Tibet,"

00:30:39.260 --> 00:30:40.400 align:middle line:10%
about the thought form.

00:30:40.400 --> 00:30:43.070 align:middle line:10%
This is where we first get this
notion of a thought form taking

00:30:43.070 --> 00:30:43.960 align:middle line:10%
on a life of its own.

00:30:43.960 --> 00:30:47.610 align:middle line:10%
She tells this story about how
she visualized this monk, how

00:30:47.610 --> 00:30:51.610 align:middle line:10%
the monks became tangibly
visible over months of effort

00:30:51.610 --> 00:30:52.730 align:middle line:10%
to people around her.

00:30:52.730 --> 00:30:55.321 align:middle line:84%
And then it started to
take on an attitude.

00:30:55.321 --> 00:30:57.320 align:middle line:84%
And she had to go through
this tremendous effort

00:30:57.320 --> 00:31:01.640 align:middle line:84%
to dissolve it because it was
no longer this jolly monk.

00:31:01.640 --> 00:31:03.179 align:middle line:90%
It was getting malicious.

00:31:03.179 --> 00:31:04.970 align:middle line:84%
There are people who
have talked about this

00:31:04.970 --> 00:31:07.520 align:middle line:84%
and debated whether
it's real or not.

00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:10.190 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that matters
because it passes, what I call,

00:31:10.190 --> 00:31:11.180 align:middle line:90%
the duck test.

00:31:11.180 --> 00:31:12.530 align:middle line:90%
Does it walk like a duck?

00:31:12.530 --> 00:31:13.530 align:middle line:90%
Does it act like a duck?

00:31:13.530 --> 00:31:15.330 align:middle line:90%
OK, it's a duck.

00:31:15.330 --> 00:31:16.910 align:middle line:84%
And we know that
thought forms play

00:31:16.910 --> 00:31:20.540 align:middle line:84%
an important role in almost all
Eastern practices and studies.

00:31:20.540 --> 00:31:24.920 align:middle line:84%
The notion that thoughts create
a vehicle for spiritual forces

00:31:24.920 --> 00:31:27.170 align:middle line:84%
to come through, that's
the whole focus around much

00:31:27.170 --> 00:31:28.700 align:middle line:90%
of the deity worship.

00:31:28.700 --> 00:31:34.490 align:middle line:84%
So we have that notion of the
tulpa, OK, the thought form.

00:31:34.490 --> 00:31:37.400 align:middle line:84%
And that is taken on
its own kind of meme

00:31:37.400 --> 00:31:38.870 align:middle line:90%
within the internet

00:31:38.870 --> 00:31:41.360 align:middle line:84%
But then we have
the tulku, and that

00:31:41.360 --> 00:31:45.380 align:middle line:84%
is a reincarnation of
supposedly an enlightened being

00:31:45.380 --> 00:31:46.460 align:middle line:90%
or great teacher.

00:31:46.460 --> 00:31:47.990 align:middle line:90%
But they both have their idea.

00:31:47.990 --> 00:31:52.875 align:middle line:84%
They're both rooted in
the idea of an intention.

00:31:52.875 --> 00:31:56.300 align:middle line:84%
I create within my mind the
desire for this to happen,

00:31:56.300 --> 00:31:58.100 align:middle line:90%
and it will.

00:31:58.100 --> 00:32:00.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's not as complex
as people think.

00:32:00.590 --> 00:32:03.750 align:middle line:84%
I always remember my grandmother
saying she wanted two things.

00:32:03.750 --> 00:32:05.120 align:middle line:90%
One is to die in her sleep.

00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:08.810 align:middle line:84%
And the other is to be a concert
pianist in her next life.

00:32:08.810 --> 00:32:10.340 align:middle line:84%
So since she died
in her sleep, I'll

00:32:10.340 --> 00:32:12.680 align:middle line:84%
assume she'll get
the next one too.

00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:13.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:32:13.480 --> 00:32:14.396 align:middle line:90%
I'm with your grandma.

00:32:14.396 --> 00:32:17.640 align:middle line:84%
I want to be a singer
in my next life.

00:32:17.640 --> 00:32:21.770 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And so that's it, I
mean, if our thoughts are real

00:32:21.770 --> 00:32:24.680 align:middle line:84%
and they are dense enough
through repeated affirmation

00:32:24.680 --> 00:32:28.850 align:middle line:84%
and focus, then what
happens to them?

00:32:28.850 --> 00:32:29.780 align:middle line:90%
Where do they go?

00:32:29.780 --> 00:32:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And there you have a
wonderful story of dialogue

00:32:31.880 --> 00:32:35.780 align:middle line:84%
between David-Neel and
Omama and of course, it's

00:32:35.780 --> 00:32:37.340 align:middle line:84%
written in
conventional language,

00:32:37.340 --> 00:32:39.470 align:middle line:84%
so some people say it
probably didn't happen.

00:32:39.470 --> 00:32:41.870 align:middle line:84%
But my guess is she is
repeating the essence

00:32:41.870 --> 00:32:45.830 align:middle line:84%
of the conversation, rather
than it word for word.

00:32:45.830 --> 00:32:49.220 align:middle line:84%
She says, well, do these
people die simply of fear

00:32:49.220 --> 00:32:51.190 align:middle line:84%
when they do this
certain practice?

00:32:51.190 --> 00:32:53.150 align:middle line:84%
Are the demons
real or is it just

00:32:53.150 --> 00:32:55.940 align:middle line:90%
their own thoughts take over?

00:32:55.940 --> 00:32:59.750 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, when
you go into a jungle,

00:32:59.750 --> 00:33:02.150 align:middle line:84%
you can believe that
tigers aren't real,

00:33:02.150 --> 00:33:04.370 align:middle line:90%
but they can still eat you.

00:33:04.370 --> 00:33:07.292 align:middle line:84%
So there's the tigers
of our own thoughts,

00:33:07.292 --> 00:33:08.750 align:middle line:84%
and then there's
the tigers created

00:33:08.750 --> 00:33:10.080 align:middle line:90%
by the thoughts of others.

00:33:10.080 --> 00:33:11.746 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I think
everybody watching

00:33:11.746 --> 00:33:15.380 align:middle line:84%
this understands being
consumed by one's own thoughts.

00:33:15.380 --> 00:33:16.400 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Yes.

00:33:16.400 --> 00:33:19.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We've all
been at the receiving

00:33:19.340 --> 00:33:23.270 align:middle line:84%
end of the damage that
has been caused us

00:33:23.270 --> 00:33:25.970 align:middle line:84%
as a result of amplifying
our own thoughts repeatedly

00:33:25.970 --> 00:33:27.590 align:middle line:90%
in a negative direction.

00:33:27.590 --> 00:33:29.420 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And now
we're being asked,

00:33:29.420 --> 00:33:31.670 align:middle line:84%
but even are your
thoughts your own now?

00:33:31.670 --> 00:33:33.380 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
people get afraid.

00:33:33.380 --> 00:33:35.840 align:middle line:84%
That's where this gets
really scary for them

00:33:35.840 --> 00:33:39.810 align:middle line:84%
because they suddenly
realize that maybe that's not

00:33:39.810 --> 00:33:40.610 align:middle line:90%
my goal in life.

00:33:40.610 --> 00:33:41.960 align:middle line:90%
That's not what I want.

00:33:41.960 --> 00:33:43.440 align:middle line:90%
This thought isn't mine.

00:33:43.440 --> 00:33:44.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:33:44.240 --> 00:33:47.440 align:middle line:84%
And if you're living
a life on autopilot,

00:33:47.440 --> 00:33:49.730 align:middle line:84%
the likelihood the thoughts
are even less your own.

00:33:49.730 --> 00:33:50.610 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: True.

00:33:50.610 --> 00:33:53.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: If you're not
consciously choosing your days,

00:33:53.030 --> 00:33:55.092 align:middle line:84%
choosing your moments,
choosing your engagements.

00:33:55.092 --> 00:33:56.550 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
