is going to be where the
ritual and the meditation,

00:42:56.490 --> 00:42:58.910 align:middle line:84%
the visualization has taken
place over and over again.

00:42:58.910 --> 00:43:01.600 align:middle line:84%
So it's going to be
churches or temples or even

00:43:01.600 --> 00:43:06.360 align:middle line:84%
political places, places that
have been enshrined in history.

00:43:06.360 --> 00:43:07.200 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:43:07.200 --> 00:43:11.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's why you see a certain
repetitive paranormal phenomena

00:43:11.600 --> 00:43:12.400 align:middle line:90%
in some places.

00:43:12.400 --> 00:43:14.050 align:middle line:84%
Because the activity
that took place

00:43:14.050 --> 00:43:16.360 align:middle line:84%
at this one moment in time
is now enshrined there,

00:43:16.360 --> 00:43:20.180 align:middle line:84%
and it comes back on a psychic
repeating loop, if you will.

00:43:20.180 --> 00:43:21.880 align:middle line:90%
So those do exist.

00:43:21.880 --> 00:43:24.520 align:middle line:84%
I think for us as individuals,
what we have to look at

00:43:24.520 --> 00:43:27.211 align:middle line:90%
is our own connection into that.

00:43:27.211 --> 00:43:28.960 align:middle line:84%
And I say to folks,
one of the best things

00:43:28.960 --> 00:43:35.020 align:middle line:84%
to do is take a look at
your spiritual practice

00:43:35.020 --> 00:43:39.280 align:middle line:84%
and try to realize how
much of it is really yours

00:43:39.280 --> 00:43:41.260 align:middle line:84%
and how much of it is
from outside of you.

00:43:41.260 --> 00:43:43.139 align:middle line:84%
And there's an easy
way to do that.

00:43:43.139 --> 00:43:44.680 align:middle line:84%
If you belong to a
group, and I don't

00:43:44.680 --> 00:43:48.160 align:middle line:84%
care what it is, take
everything from that group,

00:43:48.160 --> 00:43:50.994 align:middle line:84%
take the pictures off
your walls, the statues

00:43:50.994 --> 00:43:53.410 align:middle line:84%
off your shrine, everything,
and just put it in some boxes

00:43:53.410 --> 00:43:59.170 align:middle line:84%
and put it in your closet for 30
days, maybe a month and a half,

00:43:59.170 --> 00:44:01.780 align:middle line:84%
two months, and just
put it away and don't

00:44:01.780 --> 00:44:04.420 align:middle line:84%
fill that space with
anything and just

00:44:04.420 --> 00:44:07.810 align:middle line:84%
notice how different you feel
when you're not constantly

00:44:07.810 --> 00:44:11.190 align:middle line:84%
being reinforced by those
images or by the music.

00:44:11.190 --> 00:44:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Oh, yeah, you have to
get rid of the CDs too.

00:44:13.960 --> 00:44:15.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: When it's just you.

00:44:15.400 --> 00:44:16.690 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Just you.

00:44:16.690 --> 00:44:20.290 align:middle line:84%
You have to be just you and just
alone with your own thoughts

00:44:20.290 --> 00:44:21.100 align:middle line:90%
and notice.

00:44:21.100 --> 00:44:22.422 align:middle line:90%
Then you'll know.

00:44:22.422 --> 00:44:24.130 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing,
if you've got friends

00:44:24.130 --> 00:44:27.700 align:middle line:84%
who are entrenched in the
various social movements

00:44:27.700 --> 00:44:29.440 align:middle line:84%
or political movements,
and they have

00:44:29.440 --> 00:44:31.810 align:middle line:84%
the posters, and the
buttons, and the bumper

00:44:31.810 --> 00:44:35.110 align:middle line:84%
stickers, and all
that, same thing.

00:44:35.110 --> 00:44:41.380 align:middle line:84%
Get rid of it for two months
and notice the withdrawal.

00:44:41.380 --> 00:44:43.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so
you've just issued

00:44:43.060 --> 00:44:45.570 align:middle line:84%
all of our lovely
viewers a challenge here.

00:44:45.570 --> 00:44:47.470 align:middle line:90%
OK, good.

00:44:47.470 --> 00:44:50.290 align:middle line:84%
OK, let's talk about
I know personally

00:44:50.290 --> 00:44:53.920 align:middle line:84%
even when we're talking
about transitory situations,

00:44:53.920 --> 00:44:55.880 align:middle line:84%
and how would this
play in, for example,

00:44:55.880 --> 00:44:58.891 align:middle line:84%
because I have a
similar situation that

00:44:58.891 --> 00:45:01.390 align:middle line:84%
occurred doing research for a
show I was doing on the Donner

00:45:01.390 --> 00:45:02.190 align:middle line:90%
party.

00:45:02.190 --> 00:45:04.330 align:middle line:84%
Gene Houston's husband,
Robert Masters,

00:45:04.330 --> 00:45:06.160 align:middle line:84%
had an experience
with dark entities

00:45:06.160 --> 00:45:09.490 align:middle line:84%
as he was researching for
some work he was doing

00:45:09.490 --> 00:45:11.410 align:middle line:90%
on the subject of witchcraft.

00:45:11.410 --> 00:45:14.636 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yes, and that's
really fascinating because--

00:45:14.636 --> 00:45:16.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: These
were his beliefs.

00:45:16.010 --> 00:45:16.930 align:middle line:90%
He was just researching.

00:45:16.930 --> 00:45:17.425 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yeah,
he was researching.

00:45:17.425 --> 00:45:19.084 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He was
entering that world.

00:45:19.084 --> 00:45:20.750 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And there's
two stories here.

00:45:20.750 --> 00:45:25.360 align:middle line:10%
One is with Gustav Davidson's
book, "Dictionary of Angels."

00:45:25.360 --> 00:45:27.010 align:middle line:10%
And same thing had
occurred to him.

00:45:27.010 --> 00:45:28.465 align:middle line:10%
He said he was
bedeviled by angels

00:45:28.465 --> 00:45:30.340 align:middle line:10%
as he's writing this
book that suddenly, he's

00:45:30.340 --> 00:45:32.454 align:middle line:10%
having these encounters
and this phenomenon.

00:45:32.454 --> 00:45:34.120 align:middle line:84%
He didn't necessarily
not believe in it.

00:45:34.120 --> 00:45:35.578 align:middle line:84%
But he didn't really
believe in it.

00:45:35.578 --> 00:45:36.820 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't his purpose.

00:45:36.820 --> 00:45:39.370 align:middle line:84%
But through the
concentrated effort,

00:45:39.370 --> 00:45:40.750 align:middle line:90%
this was happening to him.

00:45:40.750 --> 00:45:43.150 align:middle line:84%
And Masters' story was
even more frightening

00:45:43.150 --> 00:45:47.890 align:middle line:84%
because his book was, I
think eros and sexuality

00:45:47.890 --> 00:45:48.910 align:middle line:90%
and witchcraft.

00:45:48.910 --> 00:45:51.370 align:middle line:90%
Again, we're back to eros.

00:45:51.370 --> 00:45:53.710 align:middle line:90%
And got some time off.

00:45:53.710 --> 00:45:55.480 align:middle line:90%
I think it's the late '60s.

00:45:55.480 --> 00:45:58.450 align:middle line:84%
He's in the Ozarks
down in Arkansas.

00:45:58.450 --> 00:45:59.790 align:middle line:90%
And he has a cabin.

00:45:59.790 --> 00:46:01.920 align:middle line:90%
He suddenly, he realized that--

00:46:01.920 --> 00:46:04.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's not funny, except
for those of us who've seen it.

00:46:04.630 --> 00:46:10.270 align:middle line:84%
After a while, things
interrupt what you're doing.

00:46:10.270 --> 00:46:13.150 align:middle line:84%
He said he had phenomena
around the cabin that

00:46:13.150 --> 00:46:14.672 align:middle line:90%
was identical to his research.

00:46:14.672 --> 00:46:15.880 align:middle line:90%
I mean, the plants are dying.

00:46:15.880 --> 00:46:17.742 align:middle line:84%
He's got crows dropping
dead out of the air.

00:46:17.742 --> 00:46:19.450 align:middle line:84%
He doesn't even have
any cattle, but he's

00:46:19.450 --> 00:46:21.010 align:middle line:90%
got dead cows in front.

00:46:21.010 --> 00:46:22.360 align:middle line:90%
The creek's run dry.

00:46:22.360 --> 00:46:25.430 align:middle line:84%
His friends come over and say,
Robert, everybody else's place

00:46:25.430 --> 00:46:26.230 align:middle line:90%
is fine.

00:46:26.230 --> 00:46:27.620 align:middle line:84%
You got dead grass
all around here.

00:46:27.620 --> 00:46:28.420 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:46:28.420 --> 00:46:29.960 align:middle line:90%
You got to get out of here.

00:46:29.960 --> 00:46:33.080 align:middle line:84%
So he finishes the book
and things return to normal

00:46:33.080 --> 00:46:34.030 align:middle line:90%
and he gets out.

00:46:34.030 --> 00:46:37.900 align:middle line:84%
Now your viewers are going to
say, well, but that's not me.

00:46:37.900 --> 00:46:42.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's not because you're
not focusing on witchcraft.

00:46:42.010 --> 00:46:45.490 align:middle line:84%
But if your are things,
what you need to understand

00:46:45.490 --> 00:46:49.800 align:middle line:84%
is that on the psychic
level, they're a flare.

00:46:49.800 --> 00:46:53.980 align:middle line:84%
You send up a signal
flare into the invisible.

00:46:53.980 --> 00:46:56.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm here and I'm paying
attention to you.

00:46:56.170 --> 00:46:59.290 align:middle line:84%
And of course, how
does the verse go?

00:46:59.290 --> 00:47:02.800 align:middle line:84%
When you look into the
abyss, the abyss looks back.

00:47:02.800 --> 00:47:03.700 align:middle line:90%
It works both ways.

00:47:03.700 --> 00:47:06.700 align:middle line:84%
When we try to find the
face of God, the face of God

00:47:06.700 --> 00:47:07.570 align:middle line:90%
is there too.

00:47:07.570 --> 00:47:10.040 align:middle line:84%
So we want to say there's
positive things there.

00:47:10.040 --> 00:47:13.690 align:middle line:84%
But it just reinforces
in a very dramatic way

00:47:13.690 --> 00:47:16.685 align:middle line:84%
the power of our thoughts that
we're completely unaware of.

00:47:16.685 --> 00:47:17.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:47:17.560 --> 00:47:20.110 align:middle line:84%
I went through a
horrible period when

00:47:20.110 --> 00:47:23.560 align:middle line:84%
I was researching for
I had to do a 10 part

00:47:23.560 --> 00:47:27.790 align:middle line:84%
series on the Donner party at
the sesquicentennial event.

00:47:27.790 --> 00:47:30.980 align:middle line:84%
And so I had to read a
number of books on it.

00:47:30.980 --> 00:47:35.440 align:middle line:84%
And well, those were like dark
missing period of my life.

00:47:35.440 --> 00:47:36.650 align:middle line:90%
It was so awful.

00:47:36.650 --> 00:47:39.410 align:middle line:84%
Now crows didn't
fall out of the sky.

00:47:39.410 --> 00:47:41.470 align:middle line:84%
I don't think anything
horrible happened.

00:47:41.470 --> 00:47:44.350 align:middle line:84%
But it did feel as though
there was something

00:47:44.350 --> 00:47:46.270 align:middle line:84%
that had been created
there that had overtaken

00:47:46.270 --> 00:47:47.620 align:middle line:90%
my psyche for the duration.

00:47:47.620 --> 00:47:49.870 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yeah, you feel
this kind of oppressiveness.

00:47:49.870 --> 00:47:50.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:47:50.680 --> 00:47:52.138 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And
that's what happens.

00:47:52.138 --> 00:47:54.100 align:middle line:84%
Yours was very dramatic
because of the nature

00:47:54.100 --> 00:47:55.090 align:middle line:90%
of the subject matter.

00:47:55.090 --> 00:47:57.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure your viewers are
familiar with what the Donner

00:47:57.120 --> 00:47:57.920 align:middle line:90%
party is.

00:47:57.920 --> 00:48:00.295 align:middle line:84%
This is a very unfortunate
and horrible piece of history.

00:48:00.295 --> 00:48:01.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, it was.

00:48:01.170 --> 00:48:02.980 align:middle line:84%
I still remember
every image, yeah.

00:48:02.980 --> 00:48:05.063 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So we have that
we're it's very strong.

00:48:05.063 --> 00:48:07.480 align:middle line:84%
But that oppressive
this can be more subtle.

00:48:07.480 --> 00:48:11.410 align:middle line:84%
It can be the subtle
annoyance that you

00:48:11.410 --> 00:48:18.186 align:middle line:84%
find with that person
who you go for coffee,

00:48:18.186 --> 00:48:19.810 align:middle line:84%
and they look at you
when you put sugar

00:48:19.810 --> 00:48:21.790 align:middle line:90%
in it instead of honey.

00:48:21.790 --> 00:48:25.090 align:middle line:84%
It's that annoying new
ageism that you often

00:48:25.090 --> 00:48:27.800 align:middle line:84%
encounter with some people
once they've found the light.

00:48:27.800 --> 00:48:28.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:48:28.600 --> 00:48:33.160 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: We all know people,
whether it's they've stopped

00:48:33.160 --> 00:48:35.320 align:middle line:90%
smoking, stopped drinking.

00:48:35.320 --> 00:48:37.180 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing worse
than a reformed blank.

00:48:37.180 --> 00:48:39.574 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, because
then it goes into judgment

00:48:39.574 --> 00:48:40.615 align:middle line:90%
and division, separation.

00:48:40.615 --> 00:48:41.190 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yes,
that's exactly it.

00:48:41.190 --> 00:48:42.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly, yeah.

00:48:42.680 --> 00:48:43.480 align:middle line:90%
So OK.

00:48:43.480 --> 00:48:44.424 align:middle line:90%
So here's another one.

00:48:44.424 --> 00:48:45.340 align:middle line:90%
This is a similar one.

00:48:45.340 --> 00:48:49.890 align:middle line:84%
Then we're going to move on to
the how do we heal this stuff.

00:48:49.890 --> 00:48:52.304 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking of Heath
Ledger and what happened

00:48:52.304 --> 00:48:53.470 align:middle line:90%
with the actor Heath Ledger.

00:48:53.470 --> 00:48:55.053 align:middle line:10%
>>STAVISH: People
bring that up a lot.

00:48:55.053 --> 00:48:56.730 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Because
of his identity

00:48:56.730 --> 00:48:59.200 align:middle line:10%
and because he would
really get into his roles

00:48:59.200 --> 00:49:00.865 align:middle line:10%
with the Joker and
this dark force.

00:49:00.865 --> 00:49:02.240 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yeah,
this is really--

00:49:02.240 --> 00:49:04.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And dying
right after that.

00:49:04.160 --> 00:49:06.118 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Yeah, this is
an important question,

00:49:06.118 --> 00:49:11.046 align:middle line:84%
because within classical
magic, there's something

00:49:11.046 --> 00:49:12.670 align:middle line:84%
that we call assumption
of the god form

00:49:12.670 --> 00:49:14.322 align:middle line:84%
where you visualize
a deity, and you

00:49:14.322 --> 00:49:15.780 align:middle line:84%
take on the qualities
of the deity,

00:49:15.780 --> 00:49:17.290 align:middle line:90%
and you become the deity.

00:49:17.290 --> 00:49:22.840 align:middle line:84%
You see a similar practice
in Indian and Tibetan Tantra

00:49:22.840 --> 00:49:24.962 align:middle line:84%
where you visualize the
deities, and the idea

00:49:24.962 --> 00:49:26.170 align:middle line:90%
is that you become the deity.

00:49:26.170 --> 00:49:27.545 align:middle line:84%
Well, actually,
the idea there is

00:49:27.545 --> 00:49:31.060 align:middle line:84%
that you're actualizing the
qualities that are already

00:49:31.060 --> 00:49:32.860 align:middle line:90%
inherent within yourself.

00:49:32.860 --> 00:49:35.210 align:middle line:84%
So they're both more
or less the same thing.

00:49:35.210 --> 00:49:37.420 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is that these
qualities exist not only

00:49:37.420 --> 00:49:41.140 align:middle line:84%
within you, but they also
exist in others, and therefore,

00:49:41.140 --> 00:49:42.490 align:middle line:90%
out there somewhere.

00:49:42.490 --> 00:49:43.660 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:49:43.660 --> 00:49:46.330 align:middle line:84%
So when you have these
actors who are essentially

00:49:46.330 --> 00:49:48.539 align:middle line:84%
doing assumption
of the god form,

00:49:48.539 --> 00:49:50.080 align:middle line:84%
they're bringing
out these qualities,

00:49:50.080 --> 00:49:52.840 align:middle line:84%
and they're staying in
this role all the time,

00:49:52.840 --> 00:49:57.640 align:middle line:84%
that it becomes a force
that has the potential

00:49:57.640 --> 00:49:58.960 align:middle line:90%
to overwhelm them.

00:49:58.960 --> 00:50:02.200 align:middle line:84%
And Bruno and, of
course, Cliano points out

00:50:02.200 --> 00:50:04.420 align:middle line:84%
that artists and
actors in particular

00:50:04.420 --> 00:50:09.520 align:middle line:84%
are super vulnerable to this
power because of the emotion

00:50:09.520 --> 00:50:11.720 align:middle line:84%
that they use in
the imagination.

00:50:11.720 --> 00:50:12.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:50:12.520 --> 00:50:13.900 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: See, all of this
is looked around the power

00:50:13.900 --> 00:50:14.900 align:middle line:90%
of the imagination.

00:50:14.900 --> 00:50:15.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:50:15.260 --> 00:50:16.890 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: If I can
hook your imagination,

00:50:16.890 --> 00:50:18.040 align:middle line:90%
then the emotions will follow.

00:50:18.040 --> 00:50:18.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:50:18.800 --> 00:50:20.140 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And that's
why symbols and images

00:50:20.140 --> 00:50:21.160 align:middle line:90%
are so important.

00:50:21.160 --> 00:50:22.060 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:50:22.060 --> 00:50:25.900 align:middle line:84%
So actors who do this
need to be able to they

00:50:25.900 --> 00:50:28.030 align:middle line:90%
need to be able to disengage.

00:50:28.030 --> 00:50:29.470 align:middle line:90%
They need to just get rid of it.

00:50:29.470 --> 00:50:30.511 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They do, right.

00:50:30.511 --> 00:50:32.560 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: They just put
it on and play the part

00:50:32.560 --> 00:50:35.334 align:middle line:84%
and know who they
are as a person.

00:50:35.334 --> 00:50:37.750 align:middle line:84%
That's what it all comes down
to, whether you're an actor,

00:50:37.750 --> 00:50:40.194 align:middle line:84%
or whether you're a millennial
involved in social justice

00:50:40.194 --> 00:50:41.110 align:middle line:90%
and getting sucked in.

00:50:41.110 --> 00:50:43.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or an accountant
in a corporation.

00:50:43.780 --> 00:50:46.190 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Who am I?

00:50:46.190 --> 00:50:46.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:50:46.990 --> 00:50:49.280 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: That's the
question we're asking.

00:50:49.280 --> 00:51:00.520 align:middle line:84%
And each of us has to be able
to say, I am I. And what we do

00:51:00.520 --> 00:51:04.430 align:middle line:84%
is, of course, Moses, and he saw
the burning bush, and he said,

00:51:04.430 --> 00:51:05.230 align:middle line:90%
who's that?

00:51:05.230 --> 00:51:07.905 align:middle line:84%
The voice comes
back, I am that I am.

00:51:07.905 --> 00:51:09.280 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking,
well, that probably

00:51:09.280 --> 00:51:10.280 align:middle line:90%
wasn't very informative.

00:51:10.280 --> 00:51:14.290 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is I am that
which is becoming I am.

00:51:14.290 --> 00:51:15.400 align:middle line:90%
I am existence.

00:51:15.400 --> 00:51:17.230 align:middle line:90%
I am.

00:51:17.230 --> 00:51:19.230 align:middle line:90%
Most of us don't say that.

00:51:19.230 --> 00:51:23.500 align:middle line:84%
What we do is we engage
in a kind of self hypnosis

00:51:23.500 --> 00:51:26.680 align:middle line:84%
is we say, I am and then
we fill in the blank.

00:51:26.680 --> 00:51:29.890 align:middle line:84%
And notice if you try
that, just relax and say,

00:51:29.890 --> 00:51:32.970 align:middle line:84%
I am, and notice how
quickly your mind

00:51:32.970 --> 00:51:33.970 align:middle line:90%
wants to fill the blank.

00:51:33.970 --> 00:51:34.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:51:34.770 --> 00:51:35.800 align:middle line:90%
I a dad, right?

00:51:35.800 --> 00:51:36.640 align:middle line:90%
I am a writer.

00:51:36.640 --> 00:51:37.240 align:middle line:90%
I am--

00:51:37.240 --> 00:51:38.365 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: All these roles.

00:51:38.365 --> 00:51:40.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --all these
externals, roles, yeah.

00:51:40.280 --> 00:51:41.696 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And
that's what happens

00:51:41.696 --> 00:51:44.290 align:middle line:84%
with actors is if you're
playing these parts,

00:51:44.290 --> 00:51:45.790 align:middle line:90%
you need to disengage.

00:51:45.790 --> 00:51:47.610 align:middle line:84%
But occultists
and metaphysicians

00:51:47.610 --> 00:51:49.900 align:middle line:84%
and spiritual people too,
because the imagination

00:51:49.900 --> 00:51:53.710 align:middle line:84%
is so powerful, it's
very easy to begin

00:51:53.710 --> 00:51:55.270 align:middle line:90%
to believe your own propaganda.

00:51:55.270 --> 00:51:56.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Indeed.

00:51:56.680 --> 00:51:59.900 align:middle line:84%
And so now looking at it on the
bright side of, like you said,

00:51:59.900 --> 00:52:00.700 align:middle line:90%
I am.

00:52:00.700 --> 00:52:04.630 align:middle line:84%
That's one exercise, beginning
to determine what you am,

00:52:04.630 --> 00:52:05.730 align:middle line:90%
what you are.

00:52:05.730 --> 00:52:08.620 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking of
this, an example that's

00:52:08.620 --> 00:52:10.310 align:middle line:90%
really beautiful to me.

00:52:10.310 --> 00:52:11.590 align:middle line:90%
I have this dear friend.

00:52:11.590 --> 00:52:15.020 align:middle line:84%
He's a pop star out of
England named Craig David.

00:52:15.020 --> 00:52:18.460 align:middle line:84%
And he's just this
amazing human being.

00:52:18.460 --> 00:52:22.150 align:middle line:10%
And we met initially because
he watches all my shows,

00:52:22.150 --> 00:52:25.410 align:middle line:10%
which helped him with his
newest album really transform

00:52:25.410 --> 00:52:27.440 align:middle line:10%
and up his game even more.

00:52:27.440 --> 00:52:30.430 align:middle line:84%
And the one thing in his story
that was so beautiful to me

00:52:30.430 --> 00:52:32.780 align:middle line:90%
is that he's in England.

00:52:32.780 --> 00:52:39.580 align:middle line:84%
He's living in Southampton,
council houses, public housing.

00:52:39.580 --> 00:52:41.680 align:middle line:90%
And the buddies like to go out.

00:52:41.680 --> 00:52:42.490 align:middle line:90%
They want to drink.

00:52:42.490 --> 00:52:44.170 align:middle line:84%
At a young age,
the whole thing is

00:52:44.170 --> 00:52:47.560 align:middle line:84%
to go out and rouse up a little
bit, get drunk and so forth.

00:52:47.560 --> 00:52:52.240 align:middle line:84%
But even at a very early
age, by 16, 17, he was like,

00:52:52.240 --> 00:52:54.820 align:middle line:84%
I want to find my
voice, literally.

00:52:54.820 --> 00:52:58.120 align:middle line:84%
Beautiful voice, if you've
not seen him, beautiful.

00:52:58.120 --> 00:52:59.930 align:middle line:90%
I want to find my voice.

00:52:59.930 --> 00:53:01.510 align:middle line:84%
And so when they'd
go out, he'd say,

00:53:01.510 --> 00:53:03.301 align:middle line:84%
man, I think I'm going
to stay in and write

00:53:03.301 --> 00:53:04.360 align:middle line:90%
some lyrics tonight.

00:53:04.360 --> 00:53:06.370 align:middle line:84%
And so he managed
to keep frames,

00:53:06.370 --> 00:53:09.790 align:middle line:84%
but totally differentiated
out into the thing that

00:53:09.790 --> 00:53:11.740 align:middle line:84%
was drawing him more
than anything, which

00:53:11.740 --> 00:53:15.639 align:middle line:84%
was to learn how to
voice his voice, to learn

00:53:15.639 --> 00:53:17.680 align:middle line:84%
how to engage with his
own voice and bring it out

00:53:17.680 --> 00:53:18.610 align:middle line:90%
into the world.

00:53:18.610 --> 00:53:20.140 align:middle line:84%
And he's one of the
strongest people

00:53:20.140 --> 00:53:22.600 align:middle line:84%
I've ever seen in a world
that is just you know.

00:53:22.600 --> 00:53:28.420 align:middle line:84%
Talk about egregores of
fame, of power, of fortune,

00:53:28.420 --> 00:53:33.880 align:middle line:84%
and he never succumbed to any
of it and kept his own mind

00:53:33.880 --> 00:53:36.340 align:middle line:84%
and still has his own
mind the entire time.

00:53:36.340 --> 00:53:37.600 align:middle line:90%
To me, that was so rare.

00:53:37.600 --> 00:53:40.930 align:middle line:84%
I just fell in love with his
story and his whole person.

00:53:40.930 --> 00:53:42.204 align:middle line:90%
He's just a sweetie pie.

00:53:42.204 --> 00:53:43.870 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well,
that's a perfect story.

00:53:43.870 --> 00:53:45.869 align:middle line:84%
Because that's really all
we're asking you to do

00:53:45.869 --> 00:53:48.760 align:middle line:84%
is sit back and
reflect on your life.

00:53:48.760 --> 00:53:50.630 align:middle line:84%
Are you doing what
you want to do?

00:53:50.630 --> 00:53:52.360 align:middle line:84%
What are your goals
and aspirations?

00:53:52.360 --> 00:53:54.631 align:middle line:84%
And is what I'm
doing now helping me?

00:53:54.631 --> 00:53:55.630 align:middle line:90%
I have a son in college.

00:53:55.630 --> 00:53:58.050 align:middle line:84%
I tell him, l said,
life's about choices.

00:53:58.050 --> 00:54:00.900 align:middle line:84%
The key to success
is time management.

00:54:00.900 --> 00:54:05.380 align:middle line:84%
I said, is what you're doing now
helping you achieve your goal?

00:54:05.380 --> 00:54:07.490 align:middle line:84%
Because if it's
not, don't do it.

00:54:07.490 --> 00:54:08.526 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:54:08.526 --> 00:54:09.400 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: But that--

00:54:09.400 --> 00:54:09.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:54:09.870 --> 00:54:11.536 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: --often
requires that we then

00:54:11.536 --> 00:54:14.839 align:middle line:84%
go against know the
group, the here.

00:54:14.839 --> 00:54:16.880 align:middle line:84%
I don't like that term,
but you know what I mean.

00:54:16.880 --> 00:54:17.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, absolutely.

00:54:17.760 --> 00:54:19.330 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: And it can be family.

00:54:19.330 --> 00:54:22.060 align:middle line:90%
It can be your community.

00:54:22.060 --> 00:54:24.515 align:middle line:84%
It can be the spiritual
group that you've

00:54:24.515 --> 00:54:25.390 align:middle line:90%
gotten involved with.

00:54:25.390 --> 00:54:27.806 align:middle line:84%
It can be the political group
that you've gotten involved.

00:54:27.806 --> 00:54:34.180 align:middle line:84%
Because when you go to a tent
revival or a fantastic yoga

00:54:34.180 --> 00:54:43.370 align:middle line:84%
retreat or even some social
protest, it feels great.

00:54:43.370 --> 00:54:44.170 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:54:44.170 --> 00:54:48.287 align:middle line:90%
Because it's a hormonal event.

00:54:48.287 --> 00:54:50.620 align:middle line:84%
Adrenaline's move moving and
all this stuff's happening.

00:54:50.620 --> 00:54:51.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Your emotions
are all moving together

00:54:51.910 --> 00:54:52.826 align:middle line:90%
in the same direction.

00:54:52.826 --> 00:54:56.180 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: That's right
and you're feeling great.

00:54:56.180 --> 00:54:59.180 align:middle line:84%
And then what happens
when it's over, you crash.

00:54:59.180 --> 00:54:59.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:54:59.980 --> 00:55:02.600 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So you want to go
back and you want to get more.

00:55:02.600 --> 00:55:04.558 align:middle line:84%
But the problem is what
people don't understand

00:55:04.558 --> 00:55:10.540 align:middle line:84%
is what they're feeling
is a experience that they

00:55:10.540 --> 00:55:13.900 align:middle line:84%
can generate within themselves,
that they can experience

00:55:13.900 --> 00:55:17.620 align:middle line:84%
through their own self
realization and then self

00:55:17.620 --> 00:55:19.590 align:middle line:90%
actualization.

00:55:19.590 --> 00:55:24.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's the part I'm talking
about is the actualization.

00:55:24.010 --> 00:55:26.850 align:middle line:90%
Do what you want to do.

00:55:26.850 --> 00:55:30.250 align:middle line:84%
Now if your groups are
helping you, wonderful.

00:55:30.250 --> 00:55:34.570 align:middle line:84%
If they're not, leave
them as best you can.

00:55:34.570 --> 00:55:36.400 align:middle line:84%
You may not be able
to leave physically.

00:55:36.400 --> 00:55:39.160 align:middle line:84%
But you can begin to give
yourself that psychic space.

00:55:39.160 --> 00:55:41.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's like what
Craig David did even as a kid.

00:55:41.800 --> 00:55:43.720 align:middle line:84%
Say, hey, I'll catch up
with you later, mates.

00:55:43.720 --> 00:55:44.240 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Catch you later.

00:55:44.240 --> 00:55:45.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:55:45.280 --> 00:55:46.850 align:middle line:90%
And still follow your own path.

00:55:46.850 --> 00:55:47.650 align:middle line:90%
>>STAVISH: Yes.

00:55:47.650 --> 00:55:49.358 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this is
so hard, especially

00:55:49.358 --> 00:55:52.210 align:middle line:84%
I think now for the young
people in reactive mode.

00:55:52.210 --> 00:55:53.602 align:middle line:84%
It's so hard to
differentiate out

00:55:53.602 --> 00:55:55.060 align:middle line:84%
because they don't
know how they're

00:55:55.060 --> 00:55:57.520 align:middle line:84%
different a lot of
times any longer.

00:55:57.520 --> 00:55:58.769 align:middle line:90%
And this is challenging.

00:55:58.769 --> 00:56:01.060 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And in many ways,
it's always been that way.

00:56:01.060 --> 00:56:03.010 align:middle line:84%
We can look back through
history and see those cycles.

00:56:03.010 --> 00:56:05.290 align:middle line:84%
But the key thing is, and
you hit on it earlier,

00:56:05.290 --> 00:56:06.250 align:middle line:90%
is technology.

00:56:06.250 --> 00:56:08.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's the
technology, absolutely.

00:56:08.000 --> 00:56:09.790 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: The
technology is the real--

00:56:09.790 --> 00:56:11.860 align:middle line:84%
that is the hook,
the line, and sinker.

00:56:11.860 --> 00:56:13.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, it's
turning into news speak,

00:56:13.930 --> 00:56:16.210 align:middle line:84%
even less differentiation,
even less texture,

00:56:16.210 --> 00:56:17.950 align:middle line:90%
less expression in life.

00:56:17.950 --> 00:56:21.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, it's down to symbols
and communication by symbols.

00:56:21.860 --> 00:56:25.110 align:middle line:84%
OK, another thing you brought up
in the book that's interesting,

00:56:25.110 --> 00:56:28.150 align:middle line:84%
it was saying that as
we become, essentially,

00:56:28.150 --> 00:56:32.020 align:middle line:84%
more sectarian by
nature as religions,

00:56:32.020 --> 00:56:35.410 align:middle line:84%
throughout the world,
especially in Europe,

00:56:35.410 --> 00:56:37.690 align:middle line:84%
have really started
dropping away.

00:56:37.690 --> 00:56:41.110 align:middle line:84%
It's left a little bit of a
vacuum on one level, yeah,

00:56:41.110 --> 00:56:45.230 align:middle line:84%
the religions themselves served
as an egregore in our lives.

00:56:45.230 --> 00:56:47.560 align:middle line:84%
So how do you see
this transition

00:56:47.560 --> 00:56:51.760 align:middle line:84%
that's occurred away
from classical religions,

00:56:51.760 --> 00:56:53.830 align:middle line:84%
Catholicism in particular
throughout Europe

00:56:53.830 --> 00:57:00.040 align:middle line:84%
and Protestantism to
being freed of that?

00:57:00.040 --> 00:57:03.820 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, the problem
is what you do is, first thing,

00:57:03.820 --> 00:57:06.140 align:middle line:84%
to risk the wrath
of your viewers,

00:57:06.140 --> 00:57:11.260 align:middle line:84%
the notion of multiculturalism
that you hear in the West

00:57:11.260 --> 00:57:13.390 align:middle line:90%
has never existed.

00:57:13.390 --> 00:57:14.360 align:middle line:90%
It is a myth.

00:57:14.360 --> 00:57:17.150 align:middle line:84%
It has never existed
historically.

00:57:17.150 --> 00:57:20.950 align:middle line:84%
So what you see is this
notion of multiculturalism

00:57:20.950 --> 00:57:23.650 align:middle line:84%
actually means lowest
common denominator.

00:57:23.650 --> 00:57:25.390 align:middle line:84%
And the lowest
common denominator

00:57:25.390 --> 00:57:26.790 align:middle line:90%
then is consumerism.

00:57:26.790 --> 00:57:28.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, absolutely.

00:57:28.540 --> 00:57:33.430 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So when
we go for this lowest

00:57:33.430 --> 00:57:36.594 align:middle line:84%
level of consumerism,
people will seek meaning.

00:57:36.594 --> 00:57:38.260 align:middle line:84%
And that meaning will
take place through

00:57:38.260 --> 00:57:43.360 align:middle line:84%
various religious or spiritual
notions or political notions.

00:57:43.360 --> 00:57:47.290 align:middle line:84%
The vacuum which is
created will be filled.

00:57:47.290 --> 00:57:48.880 align:middle line:90%
There's no question about that.

00:57:48.880 --> 00:57:51.670 align:middle line:84%
There is an effort now to
fill that vacuum in some ways

00:57:51.670 --> 00:57:55.600 align:middle line:84%
with Islam
particularly in Europe.

00:57:55.600 --> 00:57:59.440 align:middle line:84%
Here, I'm not quite certain what
it's trying to be filled with.

00:57:59.440 --> 00:58:04.584 align:middle line:84%
It's an ambiguous spiritual
but not religious notion.

00:58:04.584 --> 00:58:07.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, it seems there
is a rise in fundamentalism

00:58:07.000 --> 00:58:08.291 align:middle line:90%
again though at this time.

00:58:08.291 --> 00:58:09.790 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: I'm not
really seeing it.

00:58:09.790 --> 00:58:11.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think
we hear about it.

00:58:11.200 --> 00:58:12.160 align:middle line:90%
The media says so.

00:58:12.160 --> 00:58:14.854 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not sure the numbers
actually bear that out.

00:58:14.854 --> 00:58:16.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
and maybe it's not

00:58:16.270 --> 00:58:17.770 align:middle line:84%
fair to say what
used to be called

00:58:17.770 --> 00:58:22.060 align:middle line:84%
fundamentalist churches,
the big super churches,

00:58:22.060 --> 00:58:24.430 align:middle line:84%
don't behave in the
same fundamentalist way.

00:58:24.430 --> 00:58:28.840 align:middle line:84%
It's almost more
as like Joel Osteen

00:58:28.840 --> 00:58:33.130 align:middle line:84%
having to do with a kind of
materialist fundamentalism

00:58:33.130 --> 00:58:37.870 align:middle line:84%
toward making a better life
and gaining wealth and God

00:58:37.870 --> 00:58:39.400 align:middle line:90%
shines on you.

00:58:39.400 --> 00:58:41.930 align:middle line:84%
When you're wealthy, it's
because God is shining on you.

00:58:41.930 --> 00:58:43.690 align:middle line:84%
So it really is working
its way, religion

00:58:43.690 --> 00:58:46.760 align:middle line:84%
working its way into the world
of material and consumption.

00:58:46.760 --> 00:58:49.135 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: Well, that's a
whole interesting piece of work

00:58:49.135 --> 00:58:51.620 align:middle line:84%
there because we can go back
to the new thought movement.

00:58:51.620 --> 00:58:52.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:58:52.420 --> 00:58:54.919 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: That's been really
a part of the Protestant ethos

00:58:54.919 --> 00:58:56.131 align:middle line:90%
for a long time.

00:58:56.131 --> 00:58:57.880 align:middle line:84%
But it's also part of
the New Age movement

00:58:57.880 --> 00:58:59.510 align:middle line:84%
because the notion
of it's your karma.

00:58:59.510 --> 00:59:00.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:59:00.310 --> 00:59:02.060 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: So we have
to be careful there,

00:59:02.060 --> 00:59:04.450 align:middle line:84%
because if we have karma,
which has cause and effect,

00:59:04.450 --> 00:59:07.150 align:middle line:84%
and I have the ability
do to affect my outcomes,

00:59:07.150 --> 00:59:08.480 align:middle line:90%
then it is a way because--

00:59:08.480 --> 00:59:09.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:59:09.280 --> 00:59:10.990 align:middle line:84%
It's a very interesting
line to walk

00:59:10.990 --> 00:59:15.070 align:middle line:84%
because I too believe, yeah, you
manifest what you can manifest.

00:59:15.070 --> 00:59:17.071 align:middle line:84%
That's under your power
to manifest your life.

00:59:17.071 --> 00:59:18.070 align:middle line:90%
Nothing wrong with that.

00:59:18.070 --> 00:59:21.260 align:middle line:84%
Nothing wrong with manifesting
a life of prosperity.

00:59:21.260 --> 00:59:24.382 align:middle line:84%
But now it's going
into the big tents.

00:59:24.382 --> 00:59:26.590 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And historically,
I think we've seen that.

00:59:26.590 --> 00:59:28.310 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people just
don't remember it.

00:59:28.310 --> 00:59:29.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:59:29.110 --> 00:59:31.359 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: It's like I
mentioned this psychic research

00:59:31.359 --> 00:59:33.184 align:middle line:84%
through media that
was done in the '30s.

00:59:33.184 --> 00:59:34.600 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this,
unfortunately, falls

00:59:34.600 --> 00:59:36.360 align:middle line:84%
under the domain of the
specialists to remember it.

00:59:36.360 --> 00:59:37.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I see.

00:59:37.220 --> 00:59:39.220 align:middle line:84%
>>STAVISH: And I think
that's where we're facing

00:59:39.220 --> 00:59:43.170 align:middle line:84%
is as these larger entities
collapse and people become,

00:59:43.170 --> 00:59:45.440 align:middle line:84%
we'll say, excessively
individualistic, see,

00:59:45.440 --> 00:59:47.640 align:middle line:84%
there there's a middle
ground between this.

00:59:47.640 --> 00:59:49.740 align:middle line:84%
It's not necessarily it's
just me and me alone,

00:59:49.740 --> 00:59:51.160 align:middle line:90%
this kind of anti-com--

00:59:51.160 --> 00:59:53.724 align:middle line:84%
or total absorption
in the group.

00:59:53.724 --> 00:59:55.140 align:middle line:84%
We have to have
this middle ground

00:59:55.140 --> 00:59:58.150 align:middle line:84%
where, where do people
healthily interact and help

00:59:58.150 --> 01:00:00.221 align:middle line:90%
each other in a healthy way?

01:00:00.221 --> 01:00:02.470 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're trying
to find our way with now.

01:00:02.470 --> 01:00:03.553 align:middle line:90%
We're trying to find that.

01:00:03.553 --> 01:00:05.710 align:middle line:90%
And that's the tricky part.

01:00:05.710 --> 01:00:12.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And really, it comes
down to strengthening yourself

01:00:12.220 --> 01:00:13.080 align:middle line:90%
on all levels.

01:00:13.080 --> 01:00:16.890 align:middle line:84%
And you say this in your book
along with other, as you said,

01:00:16.890 --> 01:00:18.120 align:middle line:90%
know who you are.

01:00:18.120 --> 01:00:19.410 align:middle line:90%
Take away all the symbols.

01:00:19.410 --> 01:00:20.820 align:middle line:90%
Take away the other people.

01:00:20.820 --> 01:00:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Just sit, I am, and determine
for yourself who you are.

01:00:25.350 --> 01:00:28.440 align:middle line:84%
And then you say and make all
strong and bring all of you

01:00:28.440 --> 01:00:30.480 align:middle line:90%
into harmony and in strength.

